(37, '1 N 2 D Italy and Vatican Tour (M V- IT-101)', 'Europe', 'Minivan Packages', 1, 370, 'yes', 'no', 'yes', '<p><em><strong>1N2D Italy AND VATICAN TOUR (MV-Italy-101)</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Why visit: Iconic symbol of Imperial Rome,One of the most visited tourist attractions in Rome and the World</p>\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;The Colosseum or Coliseum, also known as the Flavian Amphitheatre (Latin: Amphitheatrum Flavium; Italian: Anfiteatro Flavio or Colosseo) is an elliptical amphitheatre in the centre of the city of Rome, Italy. Built of concrete and stone, it was the largest amphitheatre of the Roman Empire, and is considered one of the greatest works of Roman architecture and engineering. It is the largest amphitheatre in the world.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The Colosseum is situated just east of the Roman Forum. Construction began under the emperor Vespasian in 70 AD, and was completed in 80 AD under his successor and heir Titus. Further modifications were made during the reign of Domitian (81&ndash;96). These three emperors are known as the Flavian dynasty, and the amphitheatre was named in Latin for its association with their family name (Flavius).</p>', 'Transporting accommodation and breakfast only\n\n 370 Euros 2 passengers\n \n 540 Euros for 4 passengers\n \n 880 Euros 8 passengers', 'MULTIPLE LANGUAGE SPEAKING DRIVER CUM GUIDE\n\n\nMALAYALEE DRIVER ALSO AVAILABLE ON REQUIST', 'Terms & Conditions for Europe tour’s\nThe package price includes\nDaily breakfast  \nPickup and drop from airport / railway station\nAll transportation in A/c car with multiple languages speaking driver cum guide\nSightseeing as per the package\nFuel, toll, parking fee and driver allowance\nApplicable taxes   No Hidden Charge\nThe package price excludes\nAny Airfare / Train fare.\nAny transportation which is not mentioned in the itinerary (0.80 cent per km will be charged for additional use of A/c car).\nAny portage at airports and hotels, tips, insurance, wine, mineral water, telephone charges, and all items of personal nature.\nEntrance fees to Amusement parks Monuments Boating charges.Etc..\nAny services not specifically mentioned in the inclusions.\nExpenses caused by factors beyond our control like rail and flight delays, roadblocks, and vehicle mal-functions, political disturbances etc.\nTerms & Conditions\n\nIf mentioned hotels not available at the time of reservation, similar hotels will be provided with your consent\nPrices are based on a minimum of 4 adults travelling together\nPrices are based on Standard Rooms.\nSurcharge is applicable for a passenger travelling alone.', 'Vatican And Rome city tour', '54c8b36c194c2vacanza.jpg', 'A', '2016-February-03', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
