(57, 15, 'Day 15:  Dubai – Kochi ', '<p>Arrive at Kochi International Airport.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '53cceb903e87eVENICE3.jpg'),
(58, 16, 'Day  01:- 15 . 05 . 2013 -  Cochin - Doha - Rome.', '<p>Assemble at Cochin International airport at 0130hrs, check-in starts at 0140hrs on QR 265, depart to Doha at 0445hrs and reach there at 0630hrs, then connect QR 87 at 0845 to Rome and reach there at 1350hrs. &nbsp;Arrive at Rome Airport &amp; get ready to enjoy Rome city tour with our English speaking guide. Rome city such as Piazza Venezia, Roman forum, coliseum, circus Maximus, Trevi fountain, pantheon, St.Peter basilica. On arrival. The tour starts by visiting the Coliseum (Outside View), symbol of Rome and once home to the gladiators. View the Roman Forums, where the ancient civilization developed. View Trevi Fountains, arguably the most beautiful fountain in all of Rome. As coaches are restricted to enter many parts of Rome, much of the tour is done on foot. Evening Dinner in Indian Restaurant. Overnight stay at Rome.</p>', '53ccd04d0c15aRome1.jpg'),
(59, 16, 'Day 02 :- 16 . 05 . 2013 - Rome - Assisi', '<p>&nbsp;After breakfast depart early morning from hotel. Upon arrival to Vatican you will meet our English speaking guide .We will proceed for Vatican City where you will be visiting Vatican Museums, Sistine Chapel, and Gallery of the Tapestries. Upon arrival at the Vatican Walls your guide will then lead you in to the Vatican Museums taking the beautiful Spiral staircase and continuing through the Gallery of the Tapestries and the Gallery of the Geographical Maps before arriving in the famous Sistine Chapel with its magnificent fresco of the Last Judgment by Michelangelo. After enjoy Papal Audience in Vatican. After blessing pick up packed lunch and proceed to Assisi by Coach. Upon arrival to Assisi Enjoy walking tour of Assisi with our English speaking guide. You will be visiting St. Maria degli Angeli: it is a large, imposing Basilica situated on the valley just below Assisi. It covers a little oratory, named Porziuncola, where Francis and his companions first came to live in simple huts. It represents the beginning of the Franciscan communities. St. Clare Basilica: Clare is the founder of the order of the Poor Clares . She is buried in the crypt of this church where the Crucifix that spoke to St. Francis is also preserved. St. Francis Basilica: centre of the Franciscan spirituality and cradle of the medieval European art, the Basilica was built upon the Saint\\\\\\''s tomb. The double papal Basilica was founded by Pope Gregory IX and is an architectural masterpiece containing some of the finest paintings of medieval Italian art, from Cimabue to Giotto, Simone Martini, Pietro Lorenzetti, Jacopo Torriti and Pietro Cavallini. The frescoed cycles of the Old and New Testament and the panels on life of St. Francis reach the climax on the medieval theology whilst the Franciscan Order was growing in power. After Check in Hotel. Dinner in hotel. Overnight stay at Assisi.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '53ccd0ae46648Assisi1.jpg'),
(60, 16, 'Day  03 :- 17 . 05 . 2013 - Assisi – Venice', '<p>&nbsp;After breakfast proceed to Venice with coach. Upon arrival to mestre or Padova pick up Packed lunch. Coach will be parked in parking and then take ferry to Venice Island. Enjoy guided walking tour of Venice Island with our English speaking guide. Walking tour with English speaking guide. Itinerary Mark\\\\\\''s Square, St Mark\\\\\\''s Basilica from outside, Ducal Palace, Prisons, Bridge of Sighs, Rialto Bridge. After walking tour free time on Venice island. Evening back to Padova. Enjoy Indian Dinner in Restaurant. Overnight Stay at Venice.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '53ccd10f8829aVenice1.jpg'),
(61, 16, 'Day  04 :- 18 . 05 . 2013 - Venice-Padua-Milan  ', '<p>After breakfast enjoy Padova city tour with our English speaking guide, the city of St. Anthony. Where you will be visiting The Basilica of St. Anthony of Padua is more commonly just known as \\\\\\''Il Santo\\\\\\''. It is a large red-brick building with numerous bulbous domes, set to the southeast of the core of Padua. After city tour proceed to Milan. Packed lunch in padova or in Milan. After Milan city tour with our English speaking guide where you will be visiting famous sights such as the Gallery Vittorio Emanuele and the famous Cathedral of Milan with the Golden Statue of Mother Mary on the top. Dinner in Indian Restaurant. Overnight Stay at Milan.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '53ccd1a05e979Milan.jpg'),
(62, 16, 'Day 05 :- 19 . 05 . 2013 - Milan - Avignon', '<p>&nbsp;After breakfast proceed to Avignon France. Upon arrival enjoy guided tour of Avignon. Visit pope palace and other sights. Enjoy lunch on the way from Milan to Avignon. Check in hotel. Dinner in hotel. Overnight Stay at Avignon</p>', '53ccd222e9a5bAvignon1.jpg'),
(63, 16, 'Day 06 :- 20 . 05 . 2013 -  Avignon - Lourdes  ', '<p>&nbsp;After breakfast proceed to Lourdes. Upon arrival check in hotel and take your lunch. After enjoy guided walking tour of Lourdes Description: The small Pyrenees village of Lourdes, and its imposing basilica, attracts millions of pilgrims annually. This is the site where, in 1858, a young peasant girl, Bernadette Soubirous, had several famous Virgin Mary sightings. A visit to this church affords the opportunity to wander an immense cathedral, but also to see the actual cave where a young girl claimed she spoke to the Virgin Mary and where an endless stream of visitors come in search of a spiritual experience or a miraculous healing. The Catholic Church has acknowledged dozens of miracles from this spot. Rest of the day free for spiritual activity. Evening dinner in Hotel and proceed for candlelight procession. Overnight stay in Lourdes</p>', '53ccd2984f84cLourdes1.jpg'),
(64, 16, 'Day 07 :- 21 . 05 . 2013 -  Lourdes - Paris  ', '<p>&nbsp;After breakfast long distance coach from Lourdes to Paris. Packed lunch on the way to Paris. Evening arrival to Paris. Dinner in hotel. Overnight at Paris.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '53ccd3005316fParis1.jpg'),
(65, 16, 'Day 08 :- 22 . 05 . 2013 -  Paris  ', '<p>After breakfast enjoy full day city tour of Paris with our English speaking guide. &nbsp;View the incorrupt body of St Catherine Labouret whose guardian angel led her to the chapel where the Blessed Virgin displayed a vision of the miraculous medal and later the green scapular. The Virgin promised bountiful graces for all who wore these. Our sightseeing tour includes some of the most beautiful and important churches in the world such as Notre Dame Cathedral and Sacre Coeur, see the sights as the Eiffel Tower, L\\\\\\''Arc de Triomphe (entrance to 3rd level &amp; Seine River Cruise), and drive through the Champs Elysees. Enjoy other sights on this mostly panoramic tour. You will enjoy also the famous cruise on the Seine River, the best spot to see Paris! Enjoy lunch in between. Evening some free time for shopping. Dinner in Restaurant or in Hotel. Overnight &nbsp;Stay at Paris.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '53ccd3362eeddParis2.jpg'),
(66, 16, 'Day 09:- 23 . 05 . 2013 - PARIS - INTERLAKEN  ', '<p>After cold buffet breakfast at hotel long distance vehicle to transfer you from Paris &ndash; Interlaken &ndash; 607 &ndash; kms - 09:10_hrs long distance vehicle to end for the day. Local transport for hotel - dinner transfer - hotel. Transport duration 2:00 hours. Dinner at: &nbsp;Spice India, menu: 1 non veg dish, 2 vegetable dishes, 1 dal, rice, Indian bread, pickles, dessert. Overnight Stay at Interlaken.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '53ccd385ee645INTERLAKEN4.jpg'),
(67, 16, 'Day 10 :-  24 . 05 . 2013 -  INTERLAKEN', '<p>&nbsp;After the hot buffet breakfast at hotel be ready for long distance vehicle to transfer you from Interlaken to Engel berg - 86_kms - 01:15_hrs, then proceed for Cable Car at Engel berg - Titles, and return. *voucher is not required for this service * Lunch at: &nbsp;Panorama restaurant menu: * indian menu * tomato soup, spring dhoklas, bombay pav bhaji,/daal, murgh kari, basmati rice, bread, salad, mini papads, pickles,/yogurt, ajar halwa. Then later in the after noon LDC transfer you from Engelber to Lucern 36_kms - 0:30_hrs and proceed for orientation tour- city. View of Lion Monument (loewendenkmal), View of Kapellbruecke (chapel bridge), and View of Spreuerbrucke. (Spreuer bridge), Dinner at the hotel. &nbsp;Overnight Stay at Interlaken.</p>', '53ccd40ce8a21INTERLAKEN5.jpg'),
(68, 16, 'Day  11 :- 25 . 05 . 2013 -  INTERLAKEN', '<p>&nbsp;After the hot buffet breakfast at hotel long distance vehicle to transfer you to Lauterbrunnen and experience unforgettable Rack Rail Tour to Top of Europe, Jungfraujoch (13,642 FT). Lunch at: &nbsp;Bollywood menu: *indian buffet* tomatos, cucumbers, onions, yoghurt, bread, tomato soup, yellow daal, chick- peas, vegetable curry, rice, chicken curry, chocolate bar, after the fabulous tour &nbsp;LDC takes you to Engle berg for overnight stay. &nbsp;Dinner at hotel menu: buffet style long distance vehicle to end for the day.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '53ccd443a7a90INTERLAKEN6.jpg'),
(69, 16, 'Day  12 : - 26 . 05 . 2013 - INTERLAKEN – GENEVA – KUWAIT – COCHIN', '<p>Hot buffet breakfast at hotel day free for leisure and checkout the hotel and transfer you to Zurich Airport to catch QR 64 at 1600hrs which will be reaching in Doha at 2300hrs, then connect QR 264 at 2050 on 27th May and reach in cochin on 28th May at 0335am.&nbsp;</p>', '53ccd4b33ccd0INTERLAKEN7.jpg'),
(70, 20, 'Day  01:- 15 . 10 . 2013 -  Cochin - Doha - Rome', '<p>Assemble at Cochin International airport at 0130hrs, check-in starts at 0140hrs on QR 265, depart to Doha at 0445hrs and reach there at 0630hrs, then connect QR 87 at 0845 to Rome and reach there at 1350hrs. &nbsp;Arrive at Rome Airport &amp; get ready to enjoy Rome city tour with our English speaking guide. Rome city such as Piazza Venezia, Roman forum, coliseum, circus Maximus, Trevi fountain, pantheon, St.Peter basilica. On arrival. The tour starts by visiting the Coliseum (Outside View), symbol of Rome and once home to the gladiators. View the Roman Forums, where the ancient civilization developed. View Trevi Fountains, arguably the most beautiful fountain in all of Rome. As coaches are restricted to enter many parts of Rome, much of the tour is done on foot. Evening Dinner in Indian Restaurant. Overnight stay at Rome.</p>', '53ccbe29b6752rome.jpg'),
(71, 20, 'Day  02:- 16 . 10 . 2013 - Rome-Assisi', '<p>After breakfast depart early morning from hotel. Upon arrival to Vatican you will meet our English speaking guide .We will proceed for Vatican City where you will be visiting Vatican Museums, Sistine Chapel, and Gallery of the Tapestries. Upon arrival at the Vatican Walls your guide will then lead you in to the Vatican Museums taking the beautiful Spiral staircase and continuing through the Gallery of the Tapestries and the Gallery of the Geographical Maps before arriving in the famous Sistine Chapel with its magnificent fresco of the Last Judgment by Michelangelo. After enjoy Papal Audience in Vatican. After blessing pick up packed lunch and proceed to Assisi by Coach. Upon arrival to Assisi Enjoy walking tour of Assisi with our English speaking guide. You will be visiting St. Maria degli Angeli: it is a large, imposing Basilica situated on the valley just below Assisi. It covers a little oratory, named Porziuncola, where Francis and his companions first came to live in simple huts. It represents the beginning of the Franciscan communities. St. Clare Basilica: Clare is the founder of the order of the Poor Clares . She is buried in the crypt of this church where the Crucifix that spoke to St. Francis is also preserved. St. Francis Basilica: centre of the Franciscan spirituality and cradle of the medieval European art, the Basilica was built upon the Saint\\''s tomb. The double papal Basilica was founded by Pope Gregory IX and is an architectural masterpiece containing some of the finest paintings of medieval Italian art, from Cimabue to Giotto, Simone Martini, Pietro Lorenzetti, Jacopo Torriti and Pietro Cavallini. The frescoed cycles of the Old and New Testament and the panels on life of St. Francis reach the climax on the medieval theology whilst the Franciscan Order was growing in power. After Check in Hotel. Dinner in hotel. Overnight stay at Assisi.</p>', '53ccbebcf3927Assisi.jpg'),
(72, 20, 'Day  03 :- 17 . 10 . 2013 - Assisi –Venice', '<p>After breakfast proceed to Venice with coach. Upon arrival to mestre or Padova pick up Packed lunch. Coach will be parked in parking and then take ferry to Venice Island. Enjoy guided walking tour of Venice Island with our English speaking guide. Walking tour with English speaking guide. Itinerary Mark\\''s Square, St Mark\\''s Basilica from outside, Ducal Palace, Prisons, Bridge of Sighs, Rialto Bridge. After walking tour free time on Venice island. Evening back to Padova. Enjoy Indian Dinner in Restaurant. Overnight Stay at Venice.</p>', '53ccbf61e64ceVenice.jpg'),
(73, 20, 'Day  04 :- 18 . 10 . 2013 - Venice-Padua-Milan', '<p>After breakfast enjoy Padova city tour with our English speaking guide, the city of St. Anthony. Where you will be visiting The Basilica of St. Anthony of Padua is more commonly just known as \\''Il Santo\\''. It is a large red-brick building with numerous bulbous domes, set to the southeast of the core of Padua. After city tour proceed to Milan. Packed lunch in padova or in Milan. After Milan city tour with our English speaking guide where you will be visiting famous sights such as the Gallery Vittorio Emanuele and the famous Cathedral of Milan with the Golden Statue of Mother Mary on the top. Dinner in Indian Restaurant. Overnight Stay at Milan.</p>', '53ccc03987d5cPadua.jpg'),
(74, 20, 'Day 05 :- 19 . 10 . 2013 - Milan - Avignon', '<p>After breakfast proceed to Avignon France. Upon arrival enjoy guided tour of Avignon. Visit pope palace and other sights. Enjoy lunch on the way from Milan to Avignon. Check in hotel. Dinner in hotel. Overnight Stay at Avignon</p>', '53ccc223bcf6eAvignon.jpg'),
