(82, 21, 'Day1: 22/11/2014', '<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;Half dy city tour. Evening &nbsp;arrive in Fiumicino airport transferred to Roma after dinner Over night stay in hotel</p>', '53d0e68993414rome.jpg'),
(83, 21, 'Day2: 23-11-14  ', '<p>08.00 After breakfast transferred to the St Peter&rsquo;s square to participate canonization&nbsp;</p>\n<p>20.00 turn back to hotel</p>', '53d0e82c210e0St-Peter’s-square.jpg'),
(84, 21, 'Day3: 24/11/14', '<p>After breakfast transferred to Vatican for thanks giving holly mass after lunch Vatican Museums, Michelangelo\\\\\\''s breathtaking Sistine Chapel. Stroll through St. Peter\\\\\\''s Square, passing Bernini\\\\\\''s famous colonnade, to visit St. Peter\\\\\\''s Basilica, where you will view Michelangelo\\\\\\''s Pieta.</p>', '53d0e9812a0fcMichelangelos-Pieta.jpg'),
(85, 21, 'Day 4: 25/11/14', '<p>After breakfast half day city tour &nbsp; &nbsp;visit San Giovanni, Santa scale, and &nbsp;Santa Maria Maggiore,San Pavolo.Coloseum &nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp;After lunch proceed to Assisi (180km)Upon arrival to Assisi enjoy guided visit to Assisi where Francis and his companions first came to live in simple huts. It represents the beginning of the Franciscan communities. Other points of big interests: St. Clare Basilica, St. Francis Basilica: centre of the Franciscan spirituality and cradle of the medieval European art, the Basilica was built upon the Saint&rsquo;s tomb..After dinner &nbsp;Hotel for overnight stay isi Assisi</p>', '53d0ed7e8fd6aSant-Maria-Maggiore.jpg'),
(86, 21, 'Day 5: 26-11-14', '<p>08.00 proceed to Pisa260 km 3hrs</p>\n<p>&nbsp;Pisathe wonders of the world The Leaning Tower of Pisa is the campanile, or freestanding bell tower, of the cathedral of the Italian city of Pisa, known worldwide for its unintended tilt to one side. It is situated behind the Cathedral and is the third oldest structure in Pisa\\''s Cathedral Square after the Cathedral and the Baptistery. The tower\\''s tilt began during construction, caused by an inadequate foundation on ground too soft on one side to properly support the structure\\''s weight. The tilt increased in the decades before the structure was completed, and gradually increased until the structure was stabilized (and the tilt partially corrected) by efforts in the late 20th and early 21st centuries. The height of the tower is 55.86 m (183.27 ft) from the ground on the low side and 56.70 m (186.02 ft) on the high side. The width of the walls at the base is 4.09 m (13.42 ft) and at the top 2.48 m (8.14 ft). Its weight is estimated at 14,500 metric tons (16,000 short tons)after indian lunch. &nbsp;Proceed to Florence (90 kms)only a photo shoot in piazza Michelangelo thanproced to Padua(250 kms) after dinner overnight stay in Padua</p>', '53d0f1391ec9fPisa.jpg'),
(87, 21, 'Day 6', '<p>07:30AM Breakfast at the hotel 8:00AM &nbsp;Visit St Anthony Church 1 Hours Free time at St Anthony Basilica 13:00PM Transfer to Indian Restaurant for Lunch When you Finish Lunch Transfer to Venice Island by Private Boat&nbsp;</p>\n<p>English Speaking guide for Venice Island Walking tour 16:30PM See glass blowing demonstration in Murano Glass Showroom 17:00PM Free time at Venice Island Return Boat Ride to Tronchetto Transfer to Milan airport for return to India with memories</p>', '53d0f24a4149cVenice-Island.jpg'),
(89, 28, 'Day 1: ', '<p>Half day city tour. 15.00 &nbsp;Arrive in Fiumicino airport transferred to Roma for half day city tour visit San Giovanni, Santa scale, and &nbsp;Santa Maria Maggiore &nbsp;After dinner proceed to hotel for overnight stay</p>', '53d1007d42cacSan-Giovanni.jpg'),
(91, 28, 'Day 2: ', '<p>Full day city tour.&nbsp;08.00 After breakfast St Peter&rsquo;s square, Vatican Museums, Michelangelo\\s breathtaking Sistine Chapel. Stroll through St. Peter\\s Square, passing Bernini\\s famous colonnade, to visit St. Peter\\s Basilica, where you will view Michelangelo\\s Pieta. After lunch, Basilica San Paolo, &nbsp; Coliseum, Piazza Venezia, Fontana di trevi etc,, &nbsp;After dinner 20.00 turn back to hotel</p>', '53d1029e36e17Basilica-San-Paolo.jpg'),
(92, 28, 'Day 3:', '<p>08.00 After breakfast transferred to the St Peter&rsquo;s square to participate PAPAL AUDIANCE</p>', '53d104b094cbaSt-Peters-square1.jpg'),
(93, 28, 'Day 4', '<p>08.00 Transfer to Assisi (180km) 10.30, 13,00 &nbsp;Upon arrival to Assisi enjoy guided visit to Assisi where Francis and his companions first came to live in simple huts. It represents the beginning of the Franciscan communities. Other points of big interests: St. Clare Basilica, St. Francis Basilica: centre of the Franciscan spirituality and cradle of the medieval European art, the Basilica was built upon the Saint&rsquo;s tomb.. After lunch Assisi----Pisa(260km)-16.30 &nbsp;18,30After dinner &nbsp;Hotel for overnight stay in Pisa</p>', '53d108f4eedc0Assisi.jpg'),
(94, 28, 'Day 5', '<p>&nbsp;08.00 Pisa --Padua &ndash;Venice 375 km</p>\n<p>07:30AM Breakfast at the hotel 8:00AM Transfer to Padova 12:00PM Arrive Padua Visit St Anthony Church 1 Hours Free time at St Anthony Basilica 13:00PM Transfer to Indian Restaurant for Lunch Padova &ndash; Venice 14:00PM When you Finish Lunch Transfer to Venice Island by Private Boat&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;English Speaking guide for Venice Island Walking tour 16:30PM See glass blowing demonstration in Murano Glass Showroom 17:00PM Free time at Venice Island 17:30PM Return Boat Ride to Tronchetto Transfer to Indian Restaurant for Dinner After Dinner Transfer to Hotel in Mestre&nbsp;</p>', '53d1e54662f4cPadova.jpg'),
(95, 28, 'Day 6', '<p>&nbsp;Venice- Postojna cave and castle (Slovenia) 220 km-(Slovenia)&nbsp;</p>\n<p>After breakfast from Padua transferred to the largest cave in the karts region and most visited show cave in all of Europe words on a page can hardly do justice to the majesty of Postojna. So far more than 20 kilometers of galleries have been found of which barely a fraction are open to the public. All the same a visit here still takes up much of a morning or an afternoon as you make your way through the most spectacular parts of the cave at first by a dinky little narrow-gauge train and then on foot. There are no stairs or difficult climbs along the path to or inside the cave so visitors with limited mobility should not have any difficulties. &nbsp;Turn back to Paduva for overnight stay</p>', '53d1eaf343354Postojna-cave-castle.jpg'),
(96, 28, 'Day 7', '<p>08,00 Padua &ndash;Milan-Lugarno &nbsp;Switzerland 330 km.07:30AM Breakfast at the hotel 8:00AM Transfer to Milan11,30 an orientation tour in Milan and visit the famous Milan cathedral after lunch Lugarno Switzerland for overnight stay in Lugarno</p>', '53d1f3dc02dabMilan-cathedral.jpg'),
(97, 28, 'Day 8', '<p>08,00Lugarno -Titles, Engel berg, Svizzera &nbsp;190km&nbsp;</p>\n<p>After a hot lunch at Panorama restaurant in Mt.Titlis you will visit the world famous Mt. Titlis. On a hair &ndash;raising and unforgettable ride to the top of Swiss Alps at 3020 m /10000 ft (30 K.M). You will switch three different cable cars, and be amazed as the scenery changes from green meadows and scenic lakes to snow clad mountains. The last leg of the ride is one of the famous Rotair, which is the world&rsquo;s first revolving cable car, on which you will get an incredibly panoramic view of the surrounding glaciers, mountains and scenery. Dinner and overnight stay in Hotel Terrace or similar &nbsp;in Zurich</p>', '53d1f53b979ecEngel-berg.jpg'),
(98, 28, 'Day 9', '<p>11, 30 Proceed to Zurich airport</p>', '53d1f8195d683Swiss-Alps.jpg'),
