(107, 29, 'Day 9', '<p>&nbsp;Engelberg 07:00AM Breakfast at the hotel 08:00AM Transfer to Schaffhausen Engelberg - Schaffhausen 10:00AM Visit Rhine Falls (Photo Stop) &amp; See Mighty Rhine Falls Schaffhausen - Titisse 11:00AM Transfer to Titisee Black forest Area by Coach 12:00PM Visit Druba Cuckoo Factory 13:00PM Enjoy Lunch at Titisse 14:00PM Free time at Lake Titisee Titisee - Strasbourg 15:00PM Transfer to Strasbourg 16:30PM Check into hotel Strasbourg 18:00PM Transfer to Indian Restaurant</p>', '53d22ba41946dRhine-Falls.jpg'),
(108, 29, 'Day 10:', '<p>Strasbourg&mdash;Paris(486 km)6.30 hrs</p>\n<p>07:00AM Breakfast at the hotel Strasbourg - &nbsp;07:30AM Transfer to Paris 14:00PM Indian Lunch &nbsp;15:00PM Transfer to Eiffel Tower TOP Level 17:00PM Visit Seine River Cruise 18:30PM Transfer to Indian Restaurant for Dinner 19:30PM Transfer to Hotel in Paris</p>', '53d22db0a7f65Eiffel-Tower.jpg'),
(109, 30, 'DAY 1:  FRANCE- PARIS', '<p>Arrival at France. Paris Charles de Gaulle International airport. You will meet our tour coordinator &nbsp;in outside with pla card after you will enjoy Paris by night tour. Where you will see all the famous&nbsp;</p>\n<p>monuments of Paris.(Depends on your arrival timings) Then you will have dinner in Indian Restaurant. Transfer to hotel for overnight stay in hotel&nbsp;</p>', '53d355a4bd61bParis.jpg'),
(110, 30, 'DAY 2:  PARIS CITY', '<p>PARIS CITY TOUR&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Enjoy the sights of Paris on a guided city tour.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Enjoy a breathtaking view of Paris from the top of Eiffel Tower (3rd Level)&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Today after breakfast proceed to and proceed by Le Shuttle to the glamorous city of Paris. Visit Champs Elyse, Arc de Triumph, The Opera, Petit Palais and Grand Palais, Les Invalids and visit&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Notre Dame Cathedral. Then visit the Shrine of Saint Vincent de Paul. His body was buried beneath the choir of the church. Vincent De Paul canonized on 1737 by Pope Clement XII, His heart&nbsp;though remained perfectly incorrupt and is now encased in a reliquary in the chapel where the apparition of the Miraculous Medal happened and where another incorrupt body of the Visionary of&nbsp;the apparition, St. Catherine Laboure also rests. Then visit Chapel of our Lady of Miraculous Medal and view the incorrupt body of St. Catherine Labouret whose guardian angel led her to the&nbsp;chapel where the blessed virgin displayed a vision of the Medal of the Immaculate Conception, is a medal, the design of which was originated by Saint Catherine Labour&eacute; following her reported&nbsp;vision of the Blessed Virgin Mary and made by goldsmith Adrien Vachette. The virgin promised bountiful graces for all who wore these Miraculous Medals. Then visit to Sacre Coure Basilica, the&nbsp;basilica of sacred heart of Jesus. Next, we proceed to visit the top of the Eiffel Tower (3rd level), from where you will have a splendid&nbsp;view of this beautiful city. Later, enjoy a romantic seine cruise as we sail past some of the historical monuments on the river Seine. Overnight at Hotel Novotel Aulnay or similar in Paris.&nbsp;</p>', '53d355de9e2deParis1.jpg'),
(111, 30, 'DAY 03: GERMANY –TITISEE', '<p>GERMANY &ndash;TITISEE, BLACK FOREST, AND COCKOO CLOCKS&nbsp;</p>\n<p>On to Hofgut Sternen-heart of the Black Forest.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>See Cuckoo Clock demonstration</p>\n<p>After the breakfast we drive into Hofgut Sternen in Germany. The Hofgut Sternen is situated in the picturesque Hell\\\\\\''s Valley (H&ouml;llental), directly at the mouth of the Ravenna Gorge. Here you\\\\\\''ll be able&nbsp;to enjoy nature all around you. This is the heart of the Black Forest, surrounded by dark fir forests, fairy tale woods and flowering meadows. Titisee synonymous with the Black Forest Cake and&nbsp;home to the Cuckoo Clocks. This place is famous for Cuckoo Clock. Get invited for a free demonstration and buy one for your home. Entrance to Cuckoo clock workshop with a guide. Later Dinner&nbsp;and overnight stay at Overnight Hotel Hofgut Sternen or similar in Hofgut Sternen, Germany.&nbsp;</p>', '53d3585828684Hofgut-Sternen.jpg'),
(112, 29, 'Day11', '<p>Full day Paris</p>\n<p>Paris 07:00AM Breakfast at the hotel 08:00AM Transfer to Paris City Center for Guided Tour.&nbsp;10:00AM English Speaking Guide for Half day City tour covering tomb St. Vincent de Paul opera house. Norte Dam Cathedral 13:00PM Indian Lunch at 14:00PM Free time at Louvre Free time for Shopping in Paris 18:00PM Indian 19:00PM transfer to Hotel</p>', '53d23ac30bdb1Paris.jpg'),
(113, 30, 'DAY 04: RHINE FALLS - MTTITLIS ', '<p>RHINE FALLS - MT TITLIS&nbsp;</p>\n<p>View the spectacular Rhine Falls in Schaffhausen.&nbsp;Mt. Titlis with its beautiful scenery and an adventurous ride up the snow-clad&nbsp;Swiss Alps in Rotair - the world\\\\\\''s first revolving cable-car.</p>\n<p>After the breakfast we drive we proceed to Schaffhausen to visit the Rhine Falls-the largest waterfalls in Europe. This location has been specially chosen for you to get a real feel of Switzerland&nbsp;between the cantons of Schaffhausen and Z&uuml;rich. Later enjoy your time in Engelberg. After a hot lunch at Panorama restaurant in Mt.Titlis you will visit the world famous Mt. Titlis. On a hair &ndash;raising&nbsp;and unforgettableride to the top of Swiss Alps at 3020 m /10000 ft (30 K.M). You will switch three different cable cars, and be amazed as the scenery changes from green meadows and scenic&nbsp;lakes to snow clad mountains. The last leg of the ride is one of the famous Rotair, which is the world&rsquo;s first revolving cable car, on which you will get an incredibly panoramic view of the surrounding&nbsp;glaciers, mountains and scenery. Dinner and overnight stay in Hotel Terrace or similar</p>', '53d358ad12ac1Rhine-Falls.jpg'),
(114, 29, 'Day 12', '<p>Paris airpor&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Rite time proceed to Paris airport</p>', '53d23cfe62a74Paris1.jpg'),
(115, 30, 'DAY 05:LIECHTENSTEIN – AUSTRIA ', '<p>LIECHTENSTEIN &ndash; AUSTRIA&nbsp;</p>\n<p>SWAROVSKI CRYSTAL MUSEUM &ndash; TRAIN RIDE IN VADUZ&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Memorable Train ride in Vaduz&hellip;. .!!!!&nbsp;Onto Innsbruck, in picturesque Austria at the crossroads of Europe.Onto Innsbruck VADUZ ck, in picturesque Austria at the crossroads of Europe.&nbsp;Visit Swarovski Museum - the headquarters of crystals.&nbsp;&nbsp;After the breakfast proceed to Liechtenstein. Liechtenstein is a small, alpine German-speaking country doubly landlocked by Switzerland and Austria. It is the last remnant of the Holy Roman&nbsp;Empire and an independent nation with very close ties to Switzerland. It enjoys a very high standard of living and is home to some incredibly beautiful mountain scenery. The principality\\\\\\''s capital,&nbsp;Vaduz, is mainly a modern city and a major centre of commerce and international banking. Enjoy your time in train ridein Vaduz. Memorable train ride along the side of Rhine River. After lunch drive&nbsp;to picturesque Austria. Arrive in Innsbruck and proceed for an orientation tour of this beautiful city. Visit the world famous Swarovski Crystal Museum. Enjoy a fascinating experience in to the \\\\\\''world of&nbsp;crystals\\\\\\''. An experience that leaves you amazed at the dazzling glitter as you walk through this museum. A great opportunity to buy a souvenir for your family. Tonight enjoy a dinner especially&nbsp;prepared for you. Overnight at Hotel Alphotel or similar, in Innsbruck</p>', '53d35a0a10005VADUZ.jpg'),
(116, 30, 'DAY 06:VENICE – PADUA', '<p>&nbsp;After breakfast transfer from Innsbruck to the Basilica of St. Antony of Padua in Italy. St.Anthony is buried in a chapel within the large Basilica built to honour him, where his tongue is displayed for veneration in a large reliquary. For, when his body was exhumed thirty years after his death, it was claimed that the tongue glistened and looked as if it was still alive and moist; apparently a further claim was made that this was a sign of his gift of preaching. St.Anthony was canonized by Pope Gregory IX on 30 May 1232, at Spoleto, Italy, less than one year after his death. St.Antony is venerated all over the world as the Patron Saint for lost articles, and is credited with many miracles involving lost people, lost things and even lost spiritual goods. The original Basilica of St.Antony was built in 1725 by the local Italian community of Istanbul, but was later demolished and replaced with the current building which was constructed on the same location. The current Basilica was built between 1906 and 1912 in Venetian Neo-Gothic style. Visit St. Mark&rsquo;s Basilica of St.Luke. After lunch proceed to Venice.Later enjoy the public boat transfer to the heart of traditional city of Venice, Visit the St.Mark&rsquo;s Square and St.Mark Cathedral. And the tomb of St.Mark inside this basilica. Then we will enjoy a guided walking tour heading to the glass blowing demonstrationn in Murano Glass Showroom. Overnight stay in Crown Plaza or similar in Padua.</p>', '53d35b07c85fcPadua.jpg'),
(117, 30, ' DAY 07: Venice- Postojna ', '<p>&nbsp;Venice- Postojna cave and castle (Slovenia) 200 km&nbsp;</p>\n<p>After breakfast from Padua transferred to the largest cave in the karts region and most visited show cave in all of Europe words on a page can hardly do justice to the majesty of Postojna. So far more than 20 kilometers of galleries have been found of which barely a fraction are open to the public. All the same a visit here still takes up much of a morning or an afternoon as you make your way through the most spectacular parts of the cave at first by a dinky little narrow-gauge train and then on foot. There are no stairs or difficult climbs along the path to or inside the cave so visitors with limited mobility should not have any difficulties.Turn back to Paduva for overnight stay</p>', '53d35b7dede68Venice-Island.jpg'),
(118, 30, ' DAY 08: FLORANCE – PISA ', '<p>Pisa the wonders of the World&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp;After breakfast proceed to Pisa, the wonders of the world The Leaning Tower of Pisa is the campanile, or freestanding bell tower, of the cathedral of the Italian city of Pisa, known worldwide for its unintended tilt to one side. It is situated behind the Cathedral and is the third oldest structure in Pisa\\\\\\''s Cathedral Square after the Cathedral and the Baptistery. The tower\\\\\\''s tilt began during construction, caused by an inadequate foundation on ground too soft on one side to properly support the structure\\\\\\''s weight. The tilt increased in the decades before the structure was completed, and gradually increased until the structure was stabilized (and the tilt partially corrected) by efforts in the late 20th and early 21st centuries. The height of the tower is 55.86 m (183.27 ft) from the ground on the low side and 56.70 m (186.02 ft) on the high side. The width of the walls at the base is 4.09 m (13.42 ft) and at the top 2.48 m (8.14 ft). Its weight is estimated at 14,500 metric tons (16,000 short tons). Later proceed to Rome. Dinner and overnight stay in Overnight at Hotel Park California or Similar in Pisa.&nbsp;</p>', '53d35d1d2b716Pisa.jpg'),
(119, 30, 'DAY 09 : PISA –ASSISI-ROMA', '<p>&nbsp;PISA &ndash;ASSISI-ROMA</p>\n<p>&nbsp;Re-live the history of Rome in this ancient city\\\\\\''s great landmarks - Marvel at the Coliseum. &nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; After breakfast we proceed from Pisa to Assisi, Assisi is the land of St. Francis and St.Clare. Here we visit the &lsquo;Porziuncula&rsquo; (the first Franciscan house), the place of his death, his house and the thorn-less rose garden. Visit the Tomb Basilica of St. Francis including the tombs of St. Francis and his disciples. This is world&rsquo;s first Basilica in the name of a saint.. Lower and upper Basilicas are filled with world famous frescoes and depict the lives of Jesus and St.Francis. Later we visit the Church of St.Clare and the famous cross of San Damiano. After lunch transfer to Rome. Visit the famous Colosseum (Outside view), St. Mary Major Basilica, Tiber river , Roman Forum, Trevi Fountain , Circus Maximus, Plaza Venezia. Then Monument of Victor Emmanuel II. Then visit Trevi Fountain. We also see Arch de Constantine, the Arch of Augustus, The Circus Maximus &amp; other important Roman Monuments. Later enjoy an Indian dinner. Dinner and overnight stay in Overnight at Hotel President / Palace / Best Western or similar, in Rome. &nbsp;DAY 10 &nbsp; WEDNESDAY Full day Rome</p>', '53d35d825fd27Assisi.jpg'),
(120, 30, 'DAY 10', '<p>&nbsp;Am transferred to the St Peter&rsquo;s square to visit the Vatican Museums and Michelangelo\\\\\\''s breathtaking Sistine Chapel. Stroll through St. Peter\\\\\\''s Square, passing Bernini\\\\\\''s famous colonnade, to visit St. Peter\\\\\\''s Basilica, where you will view Michelangelo\\\\\\''s Pieta. This highly-finished marble sculpture depicts the body of Jesus in the arms of Mary after the Crucifixion, and is considered one of the most powerfully moving works of art in the Western world after lunch, Basilica San Paolo and &nbsp;Coliseum. &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</p>', '53d35dbd75621St-Peter’s-square.jpg'),
(121, 30, 'Day 11: Full day Rome', '<p>Wednesday also in Rome 8.30 am transferred to the St Peter&rsquo;s square for the Pope audience after Lunch visit San Giovanni, Santa scale,(Holy steps), The &lsquo;Scala Santa&rsquo; located across the street where you may climb the same steps Our Lord climbed on the way to see Pontius Pilate and then visit St.Helena Church to see &lsquo;Santa Cross in Gerusalemme&rsquo; (Holy Cross of Jerusalem), fragments of Holy Cross, One nail, part of the inscription INRI, We owe these valuable relics to St.Helena, the mother of Emperor, Constantine. &amp; other important Roman Monuments. Santa Maria Maggiore. and catacomb. &nbsp;Later enjoy a dinner. Overnight at Hotel President / Palace / Best Western or similar, in Rome.</p>', '53d365fd3b383San-Giovanni.jpg'),
(122, 30, ' DAY  12: Rome to San Giovanni Rotondo', '<p>Rome to San Giovanni Rotondo</p>\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Early morning transfered to &nbsp;San Giovanni Rotondo, the cell in which Padre Pio lived and died and the crucifix in front of which he received the stigmata, while praying after Mass in the choir loft of the small Church of Our Lady of Grace on the 20th September 1918. You will enjoy mass in this wonderful old church, which sits beside a larger new church where many multi-lingual masses and celebrations take place. This new church is home to Padre Pio&rsquo;s tomb as well as an exhibition of Padre Pio&rsquo;s life in San Giovanni Rotondo and many blessed relics and garments.</p>', '53d3690561fc8Padre-Pio’s-tomb.jpg'),
(123, 30, ' Day 13: ROME – DUBAI ', '<p>Sweet Memories of grand European Pilgrimage !!!!&nbsp;</p>\n<p>After breakfast free time for shopping. Then continue towards Flumicino International&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Airport Rome for final departure. Departs from Rome at 15.25 in Emirates Airline Flight EK0098&nbsp;</p>\n<p>and arrive Dubai at 23.15 hrs.&nbsp;</p>', '53d3692e7ab4drome.jpg'),
(124, 30, 'Day 14 :  DUBAI - KOCHI ', '<p>&nbsp;Connect Emirates Airways EK0530 from Dubai International Airport to Kochi&nbsp;</p>\n<p>International Airport at 03.20 hrs. Arrive Kochi International Airport 08.55 A.M with sweet&nbsp;</p>\n<p>memories of the Grand European Tour&nbsp;</p>', '53d369d83ec30DUBAI.jpg'),
