(131, 31, ' Day 7', '<p>Continental Breakfast at the Hotel Transfer to TitTitisee &nbsp;Lunch on the Way Visit Drubba Cuckoo Factory &nbsp;Later Transfer to Zurich Area &nbsp;Dinner at Indian Restaurant &nbsp;Over Night at Zurich&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;(B.L,D)</p>', '53d3721e0f863Zurich.jpg'),
(132, 31, 'Day 8', '<p>Continental Breakfast at the Hotel Visit Mt Titlis Lunch at Titlis Lucerne Orientation tour See Lion Monuments &amp; Chapel Bridge &nbsp;Later Transfer to Engelberg &nbsp;Indian Dinner Over Night at Engelberg &nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '53d3725dd3128Mt.-Titlis_.jpg'),
(133, 31, 'Day 9', '<p>&nbsp;Continental Breakfast at the Hotel Transfer to Milan Guided Tour of Milan Enjoy Indian Lunch at Milan Transfer to Turin Visit the Chapel of the Holy Shroud See the Tomb of St.John Bosco and the&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>tomb of St.Dominic Savio Enjoy Indian Dinner at Restaurant Over Night at Turin&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;(B.L,D)</p>', '53d3729e6f1afMilan-cathedral.jpg'),
(134, 31, ' Day 10', '<p>Transfer to Venice return Boat Ride to St Marko Square Indian Lunch English Speaking Guide for Venice Island Walking tour &nbsp;See Murano Glass Show Room Transfer to Padova English&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Speaking guide for Padua Visit St Anthony Basilica Dinner at Padova Over Night at Padova&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '53d3741a258c3St-Marko-Square.jpg'),
(135, 31, 'Day 11', '<p>Continental Breakfast at the Hotel Transfer to Pisa See Leaning tower of Pisa (Photo Stop) &nbsp;Indian Lunch at Pisa Later Transfer to Assisi Enjoy Assisi Guided Tour &nbsp;Visit Assisi Upper and Lower&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Basilica Dinner at Assisi Hotel Over Night at Assisi&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;(B.L,D)</p>', '53d374445250cPisa.jpg'),
(136, 31, 'Day 12', '<p>&nbsp;Continental Breakfast at the Hotel Transfer to Rome by Coach Arrive Rome Enjoy Indian Lunch Guided tour of Catacombs Trevi Fountain, See Colosseum Outside View Visit St Helena and Holy&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Cross Visit San Giovanni Cathedral &nbsp;Enjoy Indian Dinner Over Night in Rome&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;(B.L,D)</p>', '53d37512e856cColosseum.jpg'),
(137, 31, ' Day 13', '<p>Continental Breakfast at the Hotel Transfer to St Peters Sqaure Attend Papal Audience (Only on Wednesday) Enjoy Local Lunch Afternoon Visit Vatican Musuem Enjoy Rome Guided City tour See&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Trevi Fountai, See Colosseum Outside View Evening Enjoy Indian Dinner with Wine Over Night in Rome</p>', '53d3754996545St-Peters-square1.jpg'),
(138, 31, ' Day 14', '<p>&nbsp;Continental Breakfast at the Hotel&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;Transfer to Airport&nbsp;</p>', '53d37641a8b20Trevi-Fountai.jpg'),
(139, 32, 'Day 1: Cochin-Lisbon-Fatima', '<p>&nbsp;On arrival at Lisbon our representative will welcome you at the immigration area and will help them to go through the immigrations/ customs then to exit the arrival hall to find the coach driver.\\\\\\"Entrance to the Jeronimos Monastery(Belem)including view of the Tomb of Vasco Da Gama and the cloisters. Visit St. Antony\\\\\\''s cathedral Santo Antonio (better known as saint Antony of Padua),reversed as a matchmaker,protector of young brides,and patron of lost and found,and as actually born in Lisbon,on the site of this church. Proceed to Fathima. According to the catholic church,the Virgin Mary Appeared at fatima,Portugal numerous times in 1917 to three little shepherds named Lucia,Francisco and Jacinta.Visit to basilica of our lady (is one of the most famous Marian shrines in the world) visit to house of Francisco and Jacinta. Then visit to chapel of appatitions. Dinner and overnight stay in Fatima.</p>', '53d5cea3b6480Fatima.jpg'),
(140, 32, 'Day 2: Fatima-Avila', '<p>After the breakfast, proceed for the Holy Mass and then transfer to Avila. Long distance vehicle to transfer you from to Fatima to Avila. . Visit to Santa Theresa convent is one of the two main destinations for catholic Pilgrims to Avila.(Museum not included).Entrance to Santo Tomas Monastery it has three beautiful cloisters the most notable of which is the Reyes(Kings)Cloister.(Cloister &amp; chorus only).Voucher is not required for this service.After the entire sightseeing long distance vehicle to transfer you to the hotel Dinner and Overnight stay in Salamanca or Avila.</p>', '53d5d0c0585aaAvila.jpg'),
(141, 32, 'Day 3: Avila-Madrid', '<p>Avila-Madrid- Zaragoza.&nbsp;Early breakfast at hotel long distance vehicle to commence service long distance vehicle to transfer you from Avila to Madrid is the capital and largest city of Spain. Arrive Madrid and half day sightseeing tour with guide(English speaking) Visit of Retro Park(is the one of the Largest parks of the city of Madrid, Spain).and view of Plaza Espana.(is a large square, and popular tourist destination, located in central Madrid)And View of Royal Palace(is the official residence of the Spanish Royal family at the city of Madrid, nut is only used for state ceremony). Then proceed to the Basilica de Neustria senora del pillar(better known simply as EI Pillar).It is reputed to be the first church dedicated to Mary in history and one of two major cathedrals in the heart of Zaragoza, Spain..) Dinner and Overnight stay in Zaragoza.</p>', '53d5d0f25381fMadrid1.jpg'),
(143, 32, 'Day 4: Zaragoza - Lourdes', '<p>After the breakfast proceed to Lourdes (famous for the Marian apparitions of our lady of Lourdes said to have occurred in 1858 to Bernadette Soubirous. At the time, the most prominent feature of the town was the fortified castle that rises up from a rocky escarpment at its centre. Visit to Grottos de l\\\\\\''apparition(also called Grote Massabielle is the site of st.Bernadette\\\\\\''s visions of virgin Mary in 1858)included; visit to the baths (or healing waters).Attend mass, view of Eucharistic procession and blessing of the sick included. Evening attend Candle light procession (01 hr duration)starting from the grotto. Dinner at hotel.</p>', '53d5d20d8ccd7Zaragoza.jpg'),
(144, 32, 'Day 5:  Lourdes – Paris', '<p>After the breakfast proceed to Paris. Paris is the capital and largest city of France. It is situated on the river Seine,in northern France,at the heart of the Ile-de-France region its region are the worlds leading tourism destination. Over night at Paris.</p>', '53d5d2a685f3fLourdes.jpg'),
(145, 33, 'Day 1: Rome : Monday', '<p>Arrival at Rome Fiumicino International airport. You will meet our tour coordinator / driver in outside with pla card after you will enjoy Rome by night tour. Where you will see all the famous monuments of Rome. Then You will have dinner in Indian Restaurant. Transfer to hotel for overnight stay in hotel.</p>', '53d367c29a931rome.jpg'),
(146, 32, 'Day 6:  Paris', '<p>After breakfast in Paris proceed for full day sightseeing tour with guide (English Speaking). Visit the Notre Dame Cathedral, Sacred heart Church &nbsp;Notre Dame Cathedral or simply Notre Dame, is a historic Roman Catholic Marian cathedral on the eastern half of the &Icirc;le de la Cit&eacute; in the fourth arrondissement of Paris No guiding inside the Cathedral. Visit the church in silence. And proceed for One hour Bateaux Parisians cruise on the river seine Entrance to Eiffel tower level 2 included.The tower has become the most prominent symbol of both Paris and France, often in the establishing shot of films set in the city. &nbsp;The tower is the most-visited paid monument in the world. Dinner and Overnight stay in Paris.</p>', '53d5d2e0ac073Paris1.jpg'),
(147, 32, ' Day 7: Paris_ Dijon', '<p>Paris city tour_ Dijon 320km.&nbsp;After Hot Buffet breakfast proceed for full day tour to explore the beauty of great Paris, where you will have an opportunity to see Old and Modern Paris and its world famous land marks. Some of the sightseeing is mentioned: One hour Bateaux Parisians cruise on the river seine, Visit the Notre Dame Cathedral (here kept original crown of throne of Jesus Christ), Sacred heart Church. No guiding inside the Cathedral. Visit the church in silence. Entrance to Eiffel tower level 3 included. Miraculous Medal church, St. Vincent de Paul Church and many city tours which will give you an unforgettable idea of Imperial capital Paris dinner and overnight stay in Dijon.</p>', '53d5d2fde45f5Paris.jpg'),
(148, 33, 'Day 2 : Full Day Rome', '<p>By 10.00 AM transferred to the St Peter&rsquo;s square to visit the Vatican Museums and Michelangelo\\\\\\''s breathtaking Sistine Chapel. Stroll through St. Peter\\\\\\''s Square, passing Bernini\\\\\\''s famous colonnade, to visit St. Peter\\\\\\''s Basilica, where you will view Michelangelo\\\\\\''s Pieta. This highly-finished marble sculpture depicts the body of Jesus in the arms of Mary after the Crucifixion, and is considered one of the most powerfully moving works of art in the Western world after lunch, Basilica San Paolo and Colosseum.</p>', '53d5e3533f368rome1.jpg'),
(149, 32, 'Day 8: Dijon – Interlaken', '<p>&nbsp;Dijon &ndash; Interlaken 310 km_ &nbsp;Engel berg 90 km.&nbsp;Hot buffet breakfast at hotel &nbsp;and get ready to proceed to Switzerland, the land of natural beauty, glaciers, green meadow, mountains covered with snow, Chocolates, Cheese and much more. You will have lots of Scenic beauty of Switzerland first we visit to Interlaken than Engel berg &nbsp; &nbsp;Dinner at the hotel overnight stay in Engel Berg or near</p>', '53d5d58fa16d3Dijon.jpg'),
(150, 33, 'Day 3 : Full Day Rome', '<p>Wednesday also in Rome 8.30 am transferred to the St Peter&rsquo;s square for the Pope audience after Lunch visit San Giovanni, Santa scale, &nbsp;Santa Maria Maggiore. and catacomb. After dinner proceed to hotel for overnight stay</p>', '53d5e5caebb06rome3.jpg'),
(151, 32, 'Day 9:   Engel berg -Innsbruck', '<p>Engel berg -Innsbruck.&nbsp;After the breakfast you will be proceed to Cable Car Ride at Engelberg, Mt Titlis with Ice Flyer Lunch on the Top return. Voucher is not required for this service long distance vehicle to transfer you to Lucerne 36kms 00:30hrs and View of Lion Monument (loewendenkmal),View of Spreuerbrucke.(Spreuer bridge), view of Kapellbruecke (chapel bridge),Orientation tour with no guide after the tour you will be transferred to hotel and overnight in Vaduz or innsburk&nbsp;</p>', '53d5d5fde0f40Engel-berg.jpg'),
(152, 33, 'Day 4: Rome and Assisi (185 km)', '<p>After breakfast proceeds to Assisi. Upon arrival to Assisi enjoy guided visit to Assisi where Francis and his companions first came to live in simple huts. It represents the beginning of the Franciscan communities. Other points of big interests: St. Clare Basilica, St. Francis Basilica: centre of the Franciscan spirituality and cradle of the medieval European art, the Basilica was built upon the Saint&rsquo;s tomb.</p>\n<p>After lunch transferred to &nbsp; the Frassasi Caves (Italian: Grote di Frasassi) are a remarkable karst cave system in the municipality of Genga, Italy, in the province of Ancona, Marche. They are among the most famous show caves in Italy. The caves, discovered by a group of Ancona speleologists in 1971are situated 7 kilometers (4 miles) south of Genga, near the civil parish of San Vittore .Rich in water, the cave system is particularly well endowed with stalactites and stalagmites. After dinner go to Ancona for overnight stay.</p>', '53d5e64426498Assisi.jpg'),
(153, 33, 'Day 5:  Ancona – Padova - Venice (364 km)', '<p>7:00AM Breakfast at the hotel 7:30AM Transfer to Padova 12:00PM Arrive Padua Visit St Anthony Church 1 Hours Free time at St Anthony Basilica &nbsp;13:00PM Transfer to Indian Restaurant for Lunch Padova &ndash; Venice 14:00PM When you Finish Lunch Transfer to Venice Island by Private Boat&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</p>\n<p>English Speaking guide for Venice Island Walking tour 16:30PM See glass blowing demonstration in Murano Glass Showroom 17:00PM Free time at Venice Island 17:30PM Return Boat Ride to Tronchetto Transfer to Indian Restaurant for Dinner After Dinner Transfer to Hotel in Padua&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Day5: Padua - Innsbruck ( 375 KMS ) 4:30Hr</p>\n<p>By 07:00AM Breakfast at the hotel &nbsp;07:30AM Transfer to Innsbruck 12:00PM Innsbruck and proceed for an orientation tour 12:30PM Lunch 13:30PM Transfer to Watten to Visit Swarovski 14:30PM SWAROVSKI KRISTALLWELTEN &nbsp;15:30PM Transfer to Liechtenstein 190 Km &ndash; 2:15HR Short Orientation tour of Liechtenstein Zurich 16:00PM Transfer to Zurich 18:00PM Transfer to Indian Restaurant for an Indian Dinner.</p>', '53d5e74514a8cPadova.jpg'),
(154, 33, 'Day 6 : Full Day Switzerland', '<p>Zurich 07:30AM Breakfast at hotel. &nbsp;8:00AM Transfer To Engelberg 90KMS - 1:20hr 9:30AM Arrive Engel berg Visit MT Titlis - Booking &nbsp;Indian Lunch at Top of Titlis &nbsp;13:30PM Return back with Cable Car Engel berg - Lucerne 14:50PM Transfer to Lucerne 15:30PM Enjoy Lake Lucerne Orientation tour &nbsp;See Lion Monuments &nbsp;See Chapel Bridge Free time for Shopping at Lucerne Engelberg 18:00PM Transfer To Engelberg 19:30PM Enjoy &nbsp;Dinner at Engelberg hotel.</p>', '53d5e90b6e7e4Engel-berg.jpg'),
(155, 33, 'Day 7 : Switzerland', '<p>Engelberg 07:00AM Breakfast at the hotel 08:00AM Transfer to Schaffhausen Engelberg - Schaffhausen 10:00AM Visit Rhine Falls (Photo Stop) &amp; See Mighty Rhine Falls Schaffhausen - Titisse 11:00AM Transfer to Titisee Black forest Area by Coach 12:00PM Visit Druba Cuckoo Factory 13:00PM Enjoy Lunch at Titisse 14:00PM Free time at Lake Titisee Titisee - Strasbourg 15:00PM Transfer to Strasbourg 16:30PM Check into hotel Strasbourg 18:00PM Transfer to Indian Restaurant</p>', '53d5e9cf267edRhine-Falls.jpg'),
(156, 32, 'Day 10: Innsbruck - Mestre', '<p>Innsbruck - Mestre.&nbsp;Continental breakfast at Hotel, long distance vehicle to transfer you from Innsbruck to Mestre - 380 kms- 04:30 hrs. Then proceed to Venice- Piazza San Marco by private boat (no luggage). Venice Island, guide (English speaking) for half day sightseeing tour on foot (01:30 hrs) Glass blowing display (01:30 hrs).Visit to San Marco Basilica, visit to glass factory including display of glass blowing. View of bridge of sighs. Assistant (English speaking) for Piazza San Marco Tronchetto Pier by private boat (no luggage) long distance vehicle to transfer you to Venice. Dinner at hotel: 3 course menu, long distance travel to end of the day. Overnight in Mestre.</p>', '53d5d7137efe0Innsbruck1.jpg'),
(157, 33, 'Day 8 : Strasbourg—Paris(486 km) 6.30 hrs', '<p>By 07:00AM Breakfast at the hotel Strasbourg - &nbsp;07:30AM Transfer to Paris 14:00PM Indian Lunch &nbsp;15:00PM Transfer to Eiffel Tower TOP Level 17:00PM Visit Seine River Cruise 18:30PM Transfer to Indian Restaurant for Dinner 19:30PM Transfer to Hotel in Paris&nbsp;</p>', '53d5f0432a092Paris.jpg'),
(158, 32, 'Day 11:  Mestre - Florance', '<p style=\\"text-align: justify;\\">Mestre - Pisa- Florance. Hot buffet breakfast at hotel. Long distance vehicle to transfer you from Innsbruck to Mestre 40 kms 1 hrs. Guide (English speaking) (1 hr) for city tour on foot. Guide duration (1 hr) for city on foot. Then transfer to Pisa View of Leaning tower(outside view only). 20 minutes walking distance from coach drop off point long distance vehicle for city- half day sightseeing tour with guide ( English speaking) &ndash; Hotel. Guide duration 3:00 hrs. Entrance to Ferragamo shop without reservation view of Piazza Della signori (signori square) 15 minutes walking distances from coach drop off point view of Piazzale Michelangelo. View of Ponte Vecchio, 15 minutes walking distance from coach drop off point. Dinner at hotel: 3 course menu. Overnight in Florence</p>', '53d5f209cee74Pisa.jpg'),
(159, 33, 'Day 9 : Full Day Paris', '<p>Paris 07:00AM Breakfast at the hotel 08:00AM Transfer to Paris City Center for Guided Tour&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n<p>10:00AM English Speaking Guide for Half day City tour covering tomb St. Vincent de Paul opera house. Norte Dam Cathedral 13:00PM Indian Lunch at 14:00PM Free time at Louvre Free time for Shopping in Paris 18:00PM Indian 19:00PM transfer to Hotel&nbsp;</p>', '53d5f1481e83dParis1.jpg'),
(160, 33, 'Day 10: Paris to Lourdes (850km)', '<p>Paris 06:30AM Breakfast at the hotel 7:00AM Transfer Lourdes (10 hours journey) When we reach in Lourdes Transfer to Hotel for check in. Dinner 7.30 pm&nbsp;</p>', '53d5f93d0853fLourdes.jpg'),
(161, 33, 'Day 11: Lourdes', '<p>Full day free for Religious Activity, by&nbsp;07.30 am breakfast 12.45 lunch.19.00 dinners at hotel. Free day for Religious Activity For Holly dip. Candle Light&nbsp;Procession. Holly Mass etc</p>', '53d5f89022ceaLourdes2.jpg'),
(162, 33, 'Day 12: Lourdes to Avignon (490 km) 6.30 hrs', '<p>7.30 am breakfast 08.00 proceed to Avignon&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; After lunch we visit the Papal Palace, an austere-looking fortress &nbsp;decorated inside by Simone Martini and Matteo Giovanetti, rises above the city, its belt of walls and the vestiges of a 12th century bridge on the Rh&ocirc;ne,&rdquo; according to Unesco\\''s description of the site. The city was the residence of the Popes from 1309 to 1423.At the foot of this remarkable example of Gothic architecture, the Petit Palais and the Romanesque Cathedral Notre-Dame-des-Doms complete an exceptional monumental ensemble which bears witness to the eminent role played by Avignon in Christian Europe in the 14th century.Dinner in hotel and overnight stay&nbsp;</p>', '53d6038973efeAvignon.jpg'),
(163, 33, 'Day 13: Avigion -Genoa (460 km) 6 hrs', '<p>07:00AM Breakfast at the hotel 08:00AM Transfer to Genoa 12.30 arrive in Genoa lunch on the way than visit the world famous Genoan aquarium the aquarium was originally built for Genoa Expo \\\\\\''92 (International Exhibition Genoa \\\\\\''92 Colombo \\\\\\''92), celebrating 500 years since the Genoan sailor Christopher Columbus discovered the new world. The building, which some say looks like a ship ready to head out to sea, was designed by the Genoese architect Renzo Piano of the Renzo Piano Building Workshop. The interior design and initial exhibits for the opening in 1992 were designed by Peter Chermayeff leading a design team at Cambridge Seven Associates.[ In 1998 the aquarium was expanded with the addition of a 100-metre (330 ft) ship connected by walkway to the original building dinner in hotel and overnight stay in Genoa</p>', '53d61cc57ad92GENOA.jpg'),
(164, 32, 'Day 12: Florence - Rome', '<p>Florence-Assisi- Rome.&nbsp;After breakfast at hotel, &nbsp;transfer you to Assisi. Lunch at local restaurant. Visit the the Papal Basilica of St. Francis of Assisi (lower &amp; upper basilica) is the mother church of the Roman Catholic. This basilica is one of the most important places of Christian pilgrimage in Italy. Visit the Santa Maria Degli Angeli, is a church situated in the plain at the foot of the hill of Assisi, Italy (English speaking guide for 2 hrs). Vehicle to transfer you from Assisi &ndash; Rome. Visit Basilica of Rome, The St. Peter&rsquo;s Basilica (famous as a place of pilgrimage, the basilica is the burial site of its namesake Saint Peter, one of the twelve apostles of Jesus). Dinner in Indian restaurant. Overnight in Rome.</p>', '53d5f344ce229Florence.jpg'),
(165, 33, 'Day 14: Genoa-Pisa tower-Roma (528km)', '<p>7.30 am breakfast 08.00 proceed to Pisa tower &nbsp;view the famous Piazza del Miracles with its Leaning Tower, the Baptistery, the Dome, and the Monumental Cemetery. The four monuments of this extraordinary piazza make for a unique architectural blend of Romanesque and Gothic styles .After lunch &nbsp;transferred to Rome overnight stay at hotel &nbsp;after Indian dinner</p>', '53d61d8270c2ePisa.jpg'),
(166, 33, 'Day 15 : Rome –Airport', '<p>Have a very hearty breakfast at the hotel. Pack your bags with a promise to return once again. On time our representative will transfer you to the Airport or Railway Station to board your flight or train with sweet memories of Rome</p>', '53d6228acd1d7Airport.jpg'),
(167, 32, 'Day 13: Rome', '<p>Rome. Continental breakfast in Hotel. English speaking guide for full day sightseeing. Entrance to Vatican City with Papal audience. Lunch in Indian restaurant. Entrance to Vatican Museum (The greatest museums in the world, since they display works from the immense collection built up by the Roman Catholic Church throughout the centuries including some of the most renowned classical sculptures and most important masterpieces of Renaissance art in the world) and Sistine Chapel . dinner in Indian restaurant. Overnight in Roma</p>', '53d5f3aa619cdrome.jpg');
