(168, 32, 'Day 14:  Also in Rome', '<p>Also in Rome. After breakfast visit San Giovanni, San Paolo, Santa Maria Maggiore and St. Peter\\''s Basilica, The four basilicas in Rome,than the fafous landmark of Italy the Collosseum and catacomb. After dinner&nbsp;proceed tohotel, overnight stay Rome</p>', '53d5f3f104033St-Peter’s-square.jpg'),
(169, 32, 'Day 15:', '<p>Have a very hearty breakfast at the hotel. Pack your bags with a promise to return once again. On time our representative will transfer you to the Airport to board your flight &nbsp;with sweet&nbsp;memories</p>', '53d5f5008c6cfTrevi-Fountai.jpg'),
(170, 32, 'Day 16: Dubai – Kochi', '<p>Arrive at Kochi International Airport.</p>', '53d5f521aca5bDUBAI.jpg'),
(171, 34, 'Day 1: Half day city tour', '<p>&nbsp; 15.00 &nbsp;Arrive in Fiumicino airport transferred to Roma for half day city tour visit San Giovanni, Santa scale, and &nbsp;Santa Maria Maggiore &nbsp;After dinner proceed to hotel for overnight stay(Depends the arriving timings)</p>', '53d8917c9fe7eSan-Giovanni.jpg'),
(172, 34, ' Day 2: Full day city tour ', '<p>Affter brresakfast St Peter&rsquo;s square, Vatican Museums, Michelangelo\\\\\\''s breathtaking Sistine Chapel. Stroll through St. Peter\\\\\\''s Square, passing Bernini\\\\\\''s famous colonnade, to visit St. Peter\\\\\\''s Basilica, where you will view Michelangelo\\\\\\''s Pieta. After lunch, Basilica San Paolo, &nbsp; Coliseum etc.., then transferred to Pisa &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</p>', '53d89a028595dSt-Peters-square1.jpg'),
(173, 34, 'Day 3: Pisa --Padua', '<p>Pisa-Padua&ndash;Venice 375 km</p>\n<p>07:30AM Breakfast at the hotel 8:00AM Transfer to Pisa tower upon arrival in Pisa tower view the famous Piazza del Miracles with its Leaning Tower the Baptistery the Dome and the Monumental Cemetery. The four monuments of this extraordinary piazza make for a unique architectural blend of Romanesque and Gothic styles. Than depart to Florence (only an orientation tour) then &nbsp;Padovaafter lunch Visit St Anthony Church than transfer to Venice Island by Private Boat</p>\n<p>English Speaking guide for Venice Island for walking tour.2 hrs free time at Venice Island then transfer to Indian Restaurant for Dinner after Dinner overnight stay inMestre/Padova</p>', '53d8981000a02Pisa.jpg'),
(174, 34, 'Day 4: Venice- Postojna', '<p>Venice-Postojna cave and castle (Slovenia) 220 km-(Slovenia)</p>\n<p>&nbsp;After breakfast from Padua transferred to the largest cave in the karts region and most visited show cave in all Europewords on a page can hardly do justice to the majesty ofPostojna. So far more than 20 kilometers of galleries have been found of which barely a fraction are open to the public. All the same a visit here still takes up much of a morning or an afternoon as you make your way through the most spectacular parts of the cave at first by a dinky little narrow-gauge train and then on foot. There are no stairs or difficult climbs along the path to or inside the cave so visitors with limited mobility should not have any difficulties. &nbsp;Turn back to Padua for overnight stay</p>', '53d89ad4d2106Venice-Island.jpg'),
(175, 34, 'Day 5: Padua–Milan', '<p>Padua&ndash;Milan-Lugarno Switzerland 330 km</p>\n<p>07:30AM Breakfast at the hotel then transfer to Milan11,30 an orientation tour in Milan and visit the famous Milan cathedral after lunch Lugarno Switzerland for overnight stay in Lugarno</p>', '53d89c40bd5e4Milan-cathedral.jpg'),
(176, 34, 'Day 6: Engel berg - Titisee', '<p>After the breakfast you will proceed to Cable Car Ride at Engel berg, Mt Titles with Ice Flyer. After lunch we proceed to Lucerne 36kms 00:30hrs and View of Lion Monument (loewendenkmal), View ofSpreuerbrucke. (Spreuer bridge), view of Kapell bruecke (chapel bridge), Orientation tour with no guide after the tour you will be transferred to hotel and overnight in Titisee. &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</p>', '53d89d32bcf6cEngel-berg.jpg'),
(177, 34, 'Day 7: Titisee-Paris', '<p>Titisee-Paris 620 km</p>\n<p>After breakfast proceed to view the Cuckoo and Drubba clock manufacturing unit. &nbsp;The clocks are available at &nbsp;Black Forest Clock Centre offers a wide selection of cuckoo clocks, wall clocks, grandfather clocks and here you can also see a 15 minute demonstration regarding the story of the development of the making of the cuckoo clock. The Cuckoo clocks are made in a place around 6 kilometres away from Titisee known as H&ouml;nes cuckoo clocks. They are very famous and they make original black forest clocks. Drubba was founded around 1955 in the Black Forest- Germany\\\\\\\\\\\\\\''s most popular holiday destination. &nbsp;Dinner and overnight stay in Paris.</p>', '53d8c55c8e392Titisee3.jpg'),
(178, 34, 'Day 8:  Paris City tour', '<p>After breakfast in Paris proceed for full day sightseeing tour. Visit the Notre Dame Cathedral, is a historic Roman Catholic Marian Cathedral on the eastern half of the Ile de la Cite of Paris. No guiding inside the Cathedral. Please visit the church in silence. And proceed for one hour Bateaux Parisians cruise on the river seine .Entrance to Eiffel tower. The tower has become the most prominent symbol of France. &nbsp;The tower is the most-visited paid monument in the world. Dinner and Overnight stay in Paris.</p>', '53d8bee47118cParis1.jpg'),
(179, 34, 'Day9: Paris- Airport', '<p>PARIS (CHARLES DE GAULLE)-Airport</p>\n<p>&nbsp;Have a very hearty breakfast at the hotel. Pack your bags with a promise to return once again. On timetransfer you to the Airport to board your flight with sweet memories of Europe &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</p>', '53d8c004ebc04Airport.jpg'),
(180, 35, 'Day 1: Half day city tour', '<p>15.00 &nbsp;Arrive in Fiumicino airport transferred to Roma for half day city tour visit San Giovanni, Santa scale, and &nbsp;Santa Maria Maggiore &nbsp;After dinner proceed to hotel for overnight stay(Depends the&nbsp;arriving timings)</p>', '53dc8d07ad92cSan-Giovanni.jpg'),
(181, 35, 'Day 2: Full day city tour', '<p>After breakfast St Peter&rsquo;s square, Vatican Museums, Michelangelos breathtaking Sistine Chapel. Stroll through St. Peters Square, passing Berninis famous colonnade, to visit St. Peters Basilica,&nbsp;where you will view Michelangelos Pieta. After lunch, Basilica San Paolo, &nbsp; Coliseum etc.., Overnight stay in Rome</p>', '53dc8eb3d7c77St-Peters-square1.jpg'),
(182, 35, 'Day 3: Pisa -- Florence', '<p>Pisa the wonders of the World&nbsp;</p>\n<p>After breakfast proceeds to Pisa, the wonders of the world The Leaning Tower of Pisa is the campanile, or freestanding bell tower, of the cathedral of the Italian city of Pisa, known worldwide for its&nbsp;unintended tilt to one side. It is situated behind the Cathedral and is the third oldest structure in Pisas Cathedral Square after the Cathedral and the Baptistery. The towers tilt began during&nbsp;construction, caused by an inadequate foundation on ground too soft on one side to properly support the structures weight. The tilt increased in the decades before the structure was completed,&nbsp;and gradually increased until the structure was stabilized (and the tilt partially corrected) by efforts in the late 20th and early 21st centuries. The height of the tower is 55.86 m (183.27 ft) from the&nbsp;ground on the low side and 56.70 m (186.02 ft) on the high side. The width of the walls at the base is 4.09 m (13.42 ft) and at the top 2.48 m (8.14 ft). Its weight is estimated at 14,500 metric tons&nbsp;(16,000 short tons)</p>\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;After lunch proceed to Florence. Florence is the birthplace of the Italian language the Renaissance and opera. A guided sightseeing of Florence introduces you to the citys&nbsp;Renaissance splendor. Marvel at Brunelleschi&rsquo;s masterpiece&mdash;Florence&rsquo;s massive pink white and green Duomo complemented by Giotto&rsquo;s Campanile. Then discover the church of Santa Croce&nbsp;where the tombs of Galileo and Michelangelo as well as the Dante Memorial are displayed. You&rsquo;ll also see the Palazzo Signoria which serves as an open air gallery of ancient and Renaissance&nbsp;statues. Right time turn back to hotel for overnight stay at Hotel Park California or Similar in Florence</p>', '53dc8fdd096bbPisa.jpg'),
(183, 35, ' Day 4:Florence-Venice', '<p>Florence-Venice city tour 260 km</p>\n<p>Early morning boat ride to the Island of Murano known throughout the world for its glass manufacturing industry. Visit St. Marks Square to begin a guided walking tour of romantic Venice. View the&nbsp;Golden Basilica of San Marco, the Bridge of Sighs and visit the Doges Palace, whose facade features a massive late-Gothic gate, known as the Porte Della carta , Rest of the day to exploring&nbsp;Venice only your own Optional: Gondola Ride with Music .After lunch proceed to Postojna cave and castle (Slovenia) 200 km</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; The largest cave in the karts region and most visited show cave in all of Europe, words on a page can hardly do justice to the majesty of Postojna. So far, more than 20 kilometers of galleries&nbsp;have been found, of which barely a fraction are open to the public. All the same, a visit here still takes up much of a morning or an afternoon, as you make your way through the most spectacular&nbsp;parts of the cave, at first by a dinky little narrow-gauge train, and then on foot. There are no stairs or difficult climbs along the path to or inside the cave, so visitors with limited mobility should not have&nbsp;any difficulties. Overnight stay i Postojna&nbsp;</p>', '53dc92622cd10Venice-Island.jpg'),
(184, 35, 'Day 5:Postojna-Ljubljana', '<p>Postojna-Ljubljana- Salzburg 350km</p>\n<p>Depart to Ljubljana, a city with rich historical heritage and traditions. Visit the old centre with unique mixture of Baroque and Art Nouveau architectural appearance. Proceed to Zagreb for dinner and&nbsp;overnight stay.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;All-day excursion to King Ludwig&rsquo;s fairytale castle Neuschwanstein and Oberammergau. From Munich you will first visit the smallest of three royal castles, Linderhof, which was built by King&nbsp;Ludwig II during the 19th century as a hunting lodge. Built in French Rococo style, the castle has a Moorish pavilion which can be visited during your two hour stay. On the way to castle&nbsp;Neuschwanstein you will have a short stop in Oberammergau, world-famous for its woodcarvers, richly painted houses and Passion Play.On the approach to Neuschwanstein, it will quickly become clear as to why this magnificent neo-Romanesque style castle is the best known castle in the world. It appears through the mist like&nbsp;something out of a fairytale. Overnight stay in Salzburg</p>', '53dc9afec92c7Ljubljana1.jpg'),
(185, 35, 'Day 6: Salzburg-Munich', '<p>Salzburg-Munich-Vaduz (Liechtenstein)</p>\n<p>After breakfast proceed to Munich. Discover sights such as the Pinakotheken art museums, the world famous &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Hofbrauhaus, the National Theatre with the Royal Palace, Marienplatz and the&nbsp;Viktualien market with its colorful outdoor stalls. The tour continues to the Palace of Nymphenburg, the former summer residence of the Bavarian elector princes and kings with its beautiful and&nbsp;spacious gardens. Pass through the former artist quarter of Schwabing where you may stroll along Leopold street.In the evening stroll over to the nearby Augustinerkeller for some hearty Bavarian&nbsp;fare. Sit under the old arches and on rustic wooden benches in this traditional establishment overnight stay in Vaduz(Liechtenstein)</p>', '53dc9fe320e6aMunich1.jpg'),
(186, 35, 'Day 7: Vaduz-Engel berg', '<p>Vaduz-Engel berg-Lucerne 200km</p>\n<p>After the breakfast you will proceed to Cable Car Ride at Engel berg, Mt Titles with Ice Flyer. After lunch we proceed to Lucerne 36kms 00:30hrs and View of Lion Monument (loewendenkmal),&nbsp;View of Spreuerbrucke. (Spreuer bridge), view of Kapell bruecke (chapel bridge), Orientation tour with no guide after the tour you will be transferred to hotel and overnight in Zurich</p>', '53dca0af78acaEngel-berg.jpg'),
(187, 35, 'Day8:Zurich-Airport', '<p>Have a very hearty breakfast at the hotel. Pack your bags with a promise to return once again. On time transfer you to the Airport to board your flight with sweet memories of Europe &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</p>', '53dca2f5331bcZurich.jpg'),
(188, 36, 'DAY 1: HALF DAY CITY TOUR', '<p>&nbsp;15.00 &nbsp;Arrive in Fiumicino airport transferred to Roma for half day city tour visit San Giovanni, Santa scale, and &nbsp;Santa Maria&nbsp;Maggiore. After dinner proceed to hotel for overnight stay(Depends the arriving timings)Dinner only</p>', '53eb497e18c61rome1.jpg'),
(189, 36, 'DAY 2: FULL DAY ', '<p>FULL DAY CITY TOUR</p>\n<p>&nbsp;After breakfast St Peter&rsquo;s square, Vatican Museums, Michelangelos breathtaking Sistine Chapel. Stroll through St. Peters Square,&nbsp;passing Berninis famous colonnade, to visit St. Peters Basilica, where you will view Michelangelos Pieta. After lunch, Basilica San Paolo,&nbsp;Coliseum etc.., Overnight stay in Rome (Bf and dinner)</p>', '53eb49e29c95cSt-Peters-square1.jpg'),
(190, 36, 'DAY 3: PISA-FLORENCE', '<p><strong>Pisa the wonders of the World</strong>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;After breakfast proceeds to Pisa, the wonders of the world The Leaning Tower of Pisa is the campanile, or freestanding bell tower, of the&nbsp;cathedral of the Italian city of Pisa, known worldwide for its unintended tilt to one side. It is situated behind the Cathedral and is the third oldest&nbsp;structure in Pisas Cathedral Square after the Cathedral and the Baptistery. The towers tilt began during construction, caused by an inadequate&nbsp;foundation on ground too soft on one side to properly support the structures weight. The tilt increased in the decades before the structure was&nbsp;completed, and gradually increased until the structure was stabilized (and the tilt partially corrected) by efforts in the late 20th and early 21st&nbsp;centuries. The height of the tower is 55.86 m (183.27 ft) from the ground on the low side and 56.70 m (186.02 ft) on the high side. The width of the&nbsp;walls at the base is 4.09 m (13.42 ft) and at the top 2.48 m (8.14 ft). Its weight is estimated at 14,500 metric tons (16,000 short tons)</p>\n<p>&nbsp; After lunch proceed to Florence. Florence is the birthplace of the Italian language the Renaissance and opera. A guided&nbsp;sightseeing of Florence introduces you to the citys Renaissance splendor. Marvel at Brunelleschi&rsquo;s masterpiece&mdash;Florence&rsquo;s massive pink white&nbsp;and green Duomo complemented by Giotto&rsquo;s Campanile. Then discover the church of Santa Croce where the tombs of Galileo and Michelangelo&nbsp;as well as the Dante Memorial are displayed. You&rsquo;ll also see the Palazzo Signoria which serves as an open air gallery of ancient and Renaissance&nbsp;statues. Right time turn back to hotel for overnight stay at Hotel Park California or Similar in Florence (Bf and dinner)</p>', '53eb4a831526aPisa.jpg'),
(191, 36, 'Day 4: FLORENCE-VENICE', '<p>Florence-Venice city tour 260 km</p>\n<p>&nbsp;Early morning boat ride to the Island of Murano known throughout the world for its glass manufacturing industry. Visit St. Marks Square to&nbsp;begin a guided walking tour of romantic Venice. View the Golden Basilica of San Marco, the Bridge of Sighs and visit the Doges Palace, whose&nbsp;facade features a massive late-Gothic gate, known as the Porte Della carta , Rest of the day to exploring Venice only your own Optional: Gondola&nbsp;Ride with Music .After lunch proceed to Postojna cave and castle (Slovenia) 200 km</p>\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;The largest cave in the karts region and most visited show cave in all of Europe, words on a page can hardly do justice to the majesty of&nbsp;Postojna. So far, more than 20 kilometers of galleries have been found, of which barely a fraction are open to the public. All the same, a visit here&nbsp;still takes up much of a morning or an afternoon, as you make your way through the most spectacular parts of the cave, at first by a dinky little&nbsp;narrow-gauge train, and then on foot. There are no stairs or difficult climbs along the path to or inside the cave, so visitors with limited mobility should&nbsp;not have any difficulties. Overnight stay i Postojna (Bf and dinner)</p>', '53eb4b2faaa01Venice-Island.jpg'),
(192, 36, 'DAY 5: POSTOJANA-BUDAPEST', '<p>POSTOJANA&mdash;BUDAPEST- HUNGARY 530 KM</p>\n<p>&nbsp;After breakfast proceed to &nbsp;Budapest (210km/130miles). Then- see Castle District Hall, Royal palace, Fishermen Bastion, the Holy Trinity square,&nbsp;1,5 km cave labyrinth. We will cross the Chain Bridge and go from Buda to Pest, we approach the European third largest Parliament.&nbsp;Shopping &amp; leisure time at Vaci street. &nbsp;Lets taste Hungarian cuisine. Overnight stay in Hungary.&nbsp;</p>', '53eeed23e01b9Budapest.jpg'),
(193, 36, 'DAY6: BUDAPEST-BRATISLAVA', '<p>BUDAPEST &ndash; BRATISLAVA 200Km</p>\n<p>&nbsp;After breakfast proceed to Bratislava&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;Quality sightseeing tour - see Bratislava castle, Main square &amp; city hall, Slovak National Theatre, Slovak National Gallery...Presidential&nbsp;palace...and war memorial...we combined this sightseeing. And not to forget Petrzalka district, largest housing estate in Central Europe built under&nbsp;the communist regime... Free time for shopping/relaxing/discovering.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;Little Carpathians tour - well drive north-east of Bratislava (40min drive) to visit a Red Stone castle, magnificent, well-preserved&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Renaissance/Baroque castle owned by famous families like the Fugger&rsquo;s or the Palfys, then we visit a ceramic factory in Modra, where you can buy&nbsp;an original present, and finish with a professional wine tasting of Slovak wines coming from Small Carpathians wine region. &nbsp;Overnight stay in&nbsp;Bratisalava</p>', '53eef3ba03ae1Bratislava.jpg'),
(194, 36, ' Day 7: BRATISLAVA', '<p>BRATISLAVA - BRNO - PRAGUE, CZECH REPUBLIC, 350 Km</p>\n<p>&nbsp;Transfer to Prague. We will stop in Brno ( 130km/70miles) - the second largest city in Czech republic, where we have lunch, a short sightseeing&nbsp;tour, see Spielberg Castle, St. Peters &amp; Pauls Cathedral, Main square &amp; free time for shopping. Then we continue to Prague (from Brno it is&nbsp;200km/120miles). Then we &nbsp;See Hradcany castle, Lesser town, famous gothic Charles Bridge which connects the Old Town and Mala Strana,&nbsp;Jewish Synagogues, Old Town square &amp; magnificent Old Town Hall and the famous clock, hourly showing 12 apostles.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;Our tour ends in Wenceslavs Square, centre of entertainment, lots of shopping streets and restaurants. Prague - has various names such as&nbsp;mother of cities, gold city or city of hundred spices. Overnight stay in Prague.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '53eef99fc77d7Brno.jpg'),
(195, 36, 'DAY 8: PRAGUE-VIENNA', '<p>PRAGUE - VIENNA, AUSTRIA 350 km (4 hours drive)&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;Transfer to Vienna, Austria. Lunch break and quality sightseeing tour around the Old City. See Stephans square, Stephans Cathedral, the&nbsp;Parliament, the imperial palace Hofburg, Staatsoper &amp; Burgtheater Then there is a must what every traveller coming to Vienna should try - Vienna&nbsp;coffee ( Wiener Kaffee) and Sacher cake ( Sacher Torte ). Delicious.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;A typical food is Wienerschnitzel (pork meat), why not to try it.. Overnight stay in Vienna</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '53eeff86728d8Vienna3.jpg'),
(196, 36, 'DAY9: VIENNA-AIRPORT', '<p>&nbsp;Have a very hearty breakfast at the hotel. Pack your bags with a promise to return once again. On time transfer you to the Airport to board your&nbsp;flight with sweet memories of Europe</p>', '53ef030b78730Vienna-Airport.JPG'),
(198, 38, 'Day 01 Rome', '<p style="text-align: left;">Rome.Arrive this morning in Roma Italy our tour representative receives you at Airport or Railway Station with warm and traditional welcome. You will be transferred to the pre booked hotel. Change wash and relax and then proceed to half day panoramic guided visit of Rome In the afternoon the visit continues with the famous Roman "piazze": Piazza Navona Piazza di Spagna On the right time turn back to hotel for overnight stay</p>', '54cc7ae7d329dday1.jpg'),
(199, 38, 'Day :02 Vatican City', '<p>Vatican City.After a breakfast from the hotel we can proceed to visit Vatican city.Vatican City Museums and St. Peters Basilica Vatican City also called Holy See &nbsp;is home to the Pope and the Vatican &nbsp;St. Peters Basilica and the Sistine Chapel &nbsp;and the fabulous Vatican Museums. Vatican City is easy to visit from Rome plan to spend at least a half day there.</p>\n<p>Baths of Caracalla &nbsp;At the foot of the Aventine hill are the monumental ruins of the Baths of Caracalla &nbsp;used from the Second to Sixth century AD. Taking a bath was a social event for the people of ancient Rome and the huge complex could hold up to 1600 bathers &nbsp;Besides baths &nbsp;they held an array of facilities such as a gym &nbsp;art galleries gardens and shops selling food and drinks.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>More of Romes Majestic Churches Visit Romes Cathedral San Giovanni Laterno Saint Peter in Chains with its Michelangelo statue of Moses or Santa Maria in Cosmedin with its Byzantine mosaics and the Boca della Verita. The ruins of the ancient Rome port of Ostia Antica are well worth a visit. It is a huge complex and you can easily spend several hours wandering around the old streets shops and houses. On the right time turn back to hotel for overnight stay</p>', '54cc7b223d22eday2.jpg'),
(200, 38, 'Day: 03 Coliseum and Day Palatine Hill', '<p>Coliseum and Day Palatine Hill</p>\n<p>After breakfast from the hotel we can proceed to visit Coliseum</p>\n<p>Today you visit some of Ancient Rome best monuments and ruins.The Roman Colosseum Ancient Rome&rsquo;s huge amphitheater &nbsp;was built in between 70 and 82 AD in the heart of Rome as a venue for gladiatorial and wild animal fights. Today it s one of the best and most popular monuments of Ancient Rome. See Buying Coliseum Tickets in online for ways to avoid the long ticket line. Nearby you can visit the excavations and museum on the Palatine Hill home to Roman emperors and aristocrats.</p>\n<p>Note: On Sunday, the Via dei Fori Imperially leading to the Colosseum is closed to traffic, making a nice place to walk.</p>\n<p><strong>The Roman Forum</strong>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;The Roman Forum a huge complex of ruined temples basilicas and arches was the ceremonial legal social and business center of ancient Rome. Give yourself at least two hours to wander around .Hers what to see at the Roman Forum.</p>\n<p><strong>Travis Fountain</strong>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Then see the magnificent Travis fountain completed in 1762. Toss a coin in the fountain to ensure your return to Rome.</p>\n<p><strong>Pantheon&nbsp;</strong></p>\n<p>The Pantheon the best preserved building of ancient Rome has a spectacular dome and free admission closes 7PM.&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Via Appia Antica and Catacombs</strong>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;The Via Appia Antica the major road of the ancient Roman Empire is now a regional park Parco Regionale Dell Appia Antica Visit the catacombs of San Callisto the largest and most impressive of the catacombs. Then walk or rent a bike and ride along the ancient road lined with tombs monuments and churche</p>', '54cc7d2e7ba34day3.jpg'),
(201, 38, ' Day:4', '<p style="text-align: left;">Have a very hearty breakfast at the hotel. Pack your bags with a promise to return once again. On time our representative will transfer you to the Airport or Railway Station to board your flight or train with sweet memories of Rome</p>', '54cc7de985aacday4.jpg'),
(202, 39, 'DAY 1: ', '<p style="text-align: left;">Tuesday Rome arrive in Fumicino airport (Italy) transfer to hotel. Rest of the day Rome site seeing (depends the arrival timings)San Giovanni San Paolo Santa Maria Maggiore and St. Peters Basilica The four basilicas in Rome and catacomb After dinner return to hotel for overnight stay &nbsp; with your tour director</p>', '54cc6e3ca8a19day1.jpg'),
(203, 39, 'DAY 2:', '<p style="text-align: left;">Wednesday also in Rome 8.30 am transferred to the St Peters square for the Pope audience after that visit to the Vatican Museums and Michelangelos breathtaking Sistine Chapel. Stroll through St. Peters Square passing Berninis famous colonnade to visit St. Peters Basilica where you will view Michelangelos Pieta. This highly-finished marble sculpture depicts the body of Jesus in the arms of Mary after the Crucifixion and is considered one of the most powerfully moving works of art in the Western world than visit colosseo after dinner return to hotel for overnight stay &nbsp; with your tour director.</p>', '54cc6e90d2998day2.jpg'),
(204, 39, 'DAY 3:', '<p>Thursday Assisi and Frassasi city tour. Assisi is a town in Italy in the region of Umbria. Assisi on the western side of Mt. Subasio. It is the birthplace of St. Francis. St Francis is most famous for founding (beginning) a religious order of Friars (Brothers) called the Franciscan in 1208. One of St Francis folowersSt. Clare was also born in Assisi and founded an order of religious women called the Poor Clares.The medieval city of Assisi world-renowned for its 13th-century Basilica of St. Francis and Grottos frescoes.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Evening prossed to Frassisi:The Frasassi Caves (Italian: Grote di Frasassi) are a remarkable karst cave system in the municipality of Genga Italy in the province of Ancona Marche. They are among the most famous show caves in Italy.The caves discovered by a group of Ancona speleologists in 1971are situated 7 kilometers (4 miles) south of Genga near the civil parish of San Vittore and the Genga-San Vittore railway station (Rome-Ancona line).Rich in water the cave system is particularly well endowed with stalactites and stalagmites.after dinner return to Rome overnight Stay at hotel.(BLandD)&nbsp;</p>', '54cc6eae68f91day3.jpg'),
