(208, 40, 'DAY 3:', '<p>Friday Florence and Pisa tower &amp; city tour Morning tour begins with a visit to the Academia of Fine Arts where Michelangelos David is housed. Walk to the Dome celebrated for its magnificent dome designed by Brunelleschi and view the Baptisterys renowned "Gates of Paradise" by Ghiberti. Continue to explore the open air art museum of Signori a Square ending at Ponte Vecchio known as the "Old Bridge." Enjoy the afternoon at leisure in this spectacular Renaissance city</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Evening travel through the stunning panorama of Tuscany to Pisa. En route visit a local Tuscan farm in the countryside for a wine tasting with local specialties. Upon arrival in Pisa view the famous Piazza del Miracles with its Leaning Tower the Baptistery the Dome and the Monumental Cemetery. The four monuments of this extraordinary piazza make for a unique architectural blend of Romanesque and Gothic styles. After dinner depart from Florence. Overnight stay at Rome.(BLD)</p>', '54cc6aa32e18cday3.jpg'),
