(210, 41, 'Day 1: Rome', '<p style="text-align: left;">Tuesday, Rome, arrive in Fiumicino airport (Italy), transfer to hotel. Rest of the day Rome site seeing (depends the arrival timings) St. Peters Basilica, castle sand Angelo &nbsp;Genicolence hill etc.., After dinner return to hotel for overnight stay &nbsp; with your tour director</p>', '54cb8205c8fc5day1.jpg'),
(211, 41, 'Day 2: Vatican City and Rome', '<p style="text-align: left;">&nbsp;Vatican City and Rome. Popel audience only inwednesday) also in Rome 8.30 am transferred to the St Peter&rsquo;s square for the Pope audience after that visit to the Vatican Museums and Michelangelos breathtaking Sistine Chapel. Stroll through St. Peters Square, passing Berninis famous colonnade, to visit St. Peters Basilica, where you will view Michelangelos Pieta. This highly-finished marble sculpture depicts the body of Jesus in the arms of Mary after the Crucifixion, and is considered one of the most powerfully moving works of art in the Western world than visit San Giovanni, San Paolo, Santa Maria Maggiore Colosseo and catacomb etc.. After dinner return to hotel for overnight stay</p>', '54cb8216b834eday2.jpg'),
(212, 41, 'Day: 3 Assisi Frassasi and Florence', '<p>Assisi Frassasi and Florence. Assisi is a town in Italy, in the region of Umbria. It is the birth place of St. Francis. St Francis is most famous for founding (beginning) a religious order of Friars (Brothers) called the Franciscan, in 1208. One of St Francis followers, St. Clare was also born in Assisi and founded an order of religious women called the Poor Clares. The medieval city of Assisi, world-renowned for its 13th-century Basilica of St. Francis and Grottos frescoes. Than proceed to Frassisi</p>\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; The Frasassi Caves (Italian: Grote di Frasassi) are a remarkable karst cave system in the municipality of Genga, in the province of Ancona, Marche. They are among the most famous show caves in Italy. The caves, discovered by a group of Ancona speleologists in 1971are situated 7 kilometers (4 miles) south of Genoa, near the civil parish of San Vitoria and the Genga San vittore &nbsp; railway station (Rome- line).Rich in water, the cave system is particularly well endowed with stalactites and stalagmites.</p>\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Then proceed to Florence and visit to the Academia of Fine Arts, where Michelangelos David is housed. Walk to the Duomo, celebrated for its magnificent dome designed by Brunelleschi, and view the Baptisterys renowned "Gates of Paradise" by Ghiberti. Continue to explore the open air art museum of Signoria Square ending at Ponte Vecchio, known as the "Old Bridge." Enjoy the afternoon at leisure in this spectacular Renaissance city</p>\n<p>After dinner overnight stay at hotel in Florence</p>', '54cb82268214dday3.jpg'),
(213, 41, ' Day: 4 Pisa Padova Venezia', '<p>Pisa Padova Venezia. Morning travel through the stunning panorama of Tuscany to Pisa. En route visit a local Tuscan farm in the countryside for a wine tasting with local specialties. Upon arrival in Pisa, view the famous Piazza del Miracle with its Leaning Tower, the Baptistery, the Duomo, and the Monumental Cemetery. The four monuments of this extraordinary piazza make for a unique architectural blend of Romanesque and Gothic styles.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Afternoon proceed to Padova than Venezia by train. Boat ride to the Island of Murano known throughout the world for its glass manufacturing industry. Visit St. Marks Square to begin a guided walking tour of romantic Venice. View the Golden Basilica of San Marco, the Bridge of Sighs and visit the Doges Palace, whose facade features a massive late-Gothic gate, known as the Porta Della Carta. rest of the day to exploring Venice on your own.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Optional: Gondola Ride with Music (PM). Overnight stay at Padova.</p>', '54cb82407c3efday4.jpg'),
(214, 41, 'Day : 5 Venezia Marco polo international airport', '<p style="text-align: left;">&nbsp;Day : 5 Venezia Marco polo international airport</p>\n<p>Transfer to the Venice Marco Polo airport to board return flight to your destination&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', ''),
(215, 42, 'Day 1: Tuesday', '<p style="text-align: left;">Tuesday. Rome, arrive in Fumicino airport (Italy), transfer to hotel. Rest of the day Rome site seeing (depends the arrival timing&rsquo;s) San Giovanni, San Paolo, Santa Maria Maggiore and St. Peters Basilica the four basilicas in Rome, After dinner return to hotel for overnight stay &nbsp; with highly-finished marble sculpture depicts the body of Jesus in the arms of Mary after the Crucifixion, and is considered one of the most powerfully moving works of art your tour director.(Dinner only)</p>', '54cb7fd6971ccday1.jpg'),
