(217, 42, ' Day 3: Thursday Assisi and Frassasi ', '<p>Thursday Assisi and Frassasi . Assisi is a town in Italy, in the region of Umbria, Assisi on the western side of Mt Subasio, It is the birthplace of St. Francis. St Francis is most famous for founding (beginning) a religious order of Friars (Brothers) called the Franciscan, in 1208. One of St Francis followers,St. Clare was also born in Assisi and founded an order of religious women called the Poor Clares.The medieval city of Assisi, world-renowned for its 13th-century Basilica of St. Francis and Grottos frescoes.</p>\n<p>Evening prossed to Frassisi</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The Frasassi Caves (Italian: Grotte di Frasassi) are a remarkable karts cave system in the municipality of Genga, Italy, in the province of Ancona, Marche. They are among the most famous show caves in Italy.The caves, discovered by a group of Ancona speleologists in 1971are situated 7 kilometers (4 miles) south of Genoa, near the civil parish of San Vitoria and the Genga San &nbsp;Vittore &nbsp;railway station (Rome- line).Rich in water, the cave system is particularly well endowed with stalactites and stalagmites.after dinner overnight Stay at hotel &nbsp;in Florence.</p>', '54cb7ff51c54dday3.jpg'),
(218, 42, 'Day 4: Friday, Florence and Pisa city tour', '<p>Friday, Florence and Pisa city tour. Morning tour begins with a visit to the Academia of Fine Arts, where Michelangelos David is housed. Walk to the Duomo, celebrated for its magnificent dome designed by Brunelleschi, and view the Baptisterys renowned "Gates of Paradise" by Ghiberti. Continue to explore the open air art museum of Signoria Square ending at Ponte Vecchio, known as the "Old Bridge." Enjoy the afternoon at leisure in this spectacular Renaissance city</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Evening Travel through the stunning panorama of Tuscany to Pisa, En route, visit a local Tuscan farm in the countryside for a wine tasting with local specialties. Upon arrival in Pisa, view the famous Piazza del Miracoli with its Leaning Tower, the Baptistery, the Duomo, and the Monumental Cemetery. The four monuments of this extraordinary piazza make for a unique architectural blend of Romanesque and Gothic styles. After dinner depart from Florence. Overnight stay at Venice.</p>', '54cb800cd08c0day4.jpg'),
(219, 42, 'Day 5: Saturday, Venice city tour', '<p>&nbsp;Saturday, Venice city tour. Early morning boat ride to the Island of Murano, known throughout the world for its glass manufacturing industry. Visit St. Marks Square to begin a guided walking tour of romantic Venice. View the Golden Basilica of San Marco, the Bridge of Sighs and visit the Doges Palace, whose facade features a massive late-Gothic gate, known as the Porta della Carta, Rest of the day to exploring Venice on your own.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Optional: Gondola Ride with Music (PM) Overnight stay at Venice. .</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '54cb8023b312aday5.jpg'),
