(222, 43, 'Day 2: Wednesday', '<p style="text-align: left;">&nbsp;Wednesday also in Rome 8.30 am transferred to the St Peters square for the Pope audience after that visit to the Vatican Museums and Michelangelos breathtaking Sistine Chapel. Stroll through St. Peters Square, passing Berninis famous colonnade, to visit St. Peters Basilica, where you will view Michelangelos Pieta. This highly-finished marble sculpture depicts the body of Jesus in the arms of Mary after the Crucifixion, and is considered one of the most powerfully moving works of art in the Western world, than visit colosseo after dinner return to hotel for overnight stay &nbsp; with your tour director.</p>', '54cb7c7e855d6day2.jpg'),
(223, 43, 'Day 3 Napoli and Pompeii 250 km', '<p style="text-align: left;">Napoli and Pompeii 250 km.Naples possesses many historical monuments going back almost 3,000 years, particularly the treasures, to b The old town with its narrow streets and stepped lanes and its tall balconied houses is fringed on the west and north by extensive villa suburbs and on the east by an industrial zone. In recent years much of the city has been redeveloped with new buildings and realigned streets, particularly in the area around the harbor, the Rione Santa Lucia.e seen in the National Museum, garnered from the cities engulfed by Vesuvius; the port of Naples is of major importance for southern Italy. Teatro San Carlo and the five- towered Castel Nuovo. Naples Royal Palace Castel Nuovo Santa Lucia Mt Vesuvius &nbsp;Vesuvius is the only active volcano on the European mainland. Mt Vesuvius (1281 meters) located on the eastern shore of the Bay of Naples, half an hour from Naples. When we arrived to Naples, first thing we noticed was Mount Vesuvius looming ominously in the background. It is dormant at the moment - its last eruption being in 1944 - but some scientists claim that it won&rsquo;t be long. Overnight stay in ferry.&nbsp;</p>', '54cb7c96b292aday3.jpg'),
(224, 43, 'Day 4Bari: (Embarkation)–Overnight Ferry Crossing To Patras, Greece', '<p>Bari: (Embarkation)&ndash;Overnight Ferry Crossing To Patras, Greece</p>\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp;Bari, capital of the region of Apulia and the province of the same name, lies in southern Italy - on the Adriatic coast. It is the largest city in Apulia and the second largest in southern Italy after Naples.</p>', '54cb7cafa0501day4.jpg'),
(225, 43, 'Day 5: Patras. (Disembarkation) 16 hour’s journey in ferry. Than to Nauplia 136 km', '<p>Patras. (Disembarkation) 16 hour&rsquo;s journey in ferry. Than to Nauplia 136 km</p>\n<p>&nbsp;Nafplio was the second capital of newly formed Greece after Misologgi until the capital eventually became Athens. It is an historical city due to its meaning to the Greek Revolution. It has a fantastic centre with small neoclassical historical houses, squares and churches. The Castles Palamidi Standing like a crown over Nafplio, Palamidi fortress (build by the Venetians around 1686 and completed to its present form in 1714) was so well designed that all attempts to conquer it were unsuccessful, making it a legend at the time. Finally, in 1822, the Greeks succeeded, creating surprise and amazement. In very good condition, you can visit it by taking the legendary 999 (in fact 857) stair-steps, or simply drive there. The view is unique, and you will also see many historical monuments, such as the small cave-prisons (also prison of the national hero Kolokotronis) and the church of Saint Andreas. Overnight stay here.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '54cb7cc4a54c7day5.jpg'),
(226, 43, 'Day6: Nauplia Athens- 182 km', '<p>Nauplia Athens- 182 km</p>\n<p>&nbsp;Athens is one of the oldest and most famous cities in the world. Many interesting tourist attractions can be found in Athens. Athens is rich in various buildings, monuments, and ancient art. One of the most famous is the Acropolis is to be one proof of the classical Greek art. Here are the best tourist attractions in Athens you can visit: Acropolis and Parthenon Temple National Archaeological Museum of Athens The Ancient Agora Mount Lycabettus.(B,Land,D)</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '54cb7ce658733day6.jpg'),
(227, 30, 'Day 7: Athens international airport', '<p>Have a very hearty breakfast at the hotel. Pack your bags with a promise to return once again. On time our representative will transfer you to the Airport or Railway Station to board your flight or train with sweet memories&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', ''),
(228, 43, ' Day 7: Athens international airport', '<p>Athens international airport</p>\n<p>Have a very hearty breakfast at the hotel. Pack your bags with a promise to return once again. On time our representative will transfer you to the Airport or Railway Station to board your flight or train with sweet memories</p>', '54cb7cfb47f56day7.jpg');
