(271, 50, 'Day 1: Arrive Rome', '<p>Arrive Rome</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>On arrival Rome, transfers to hotel. Check into hotel Later proceed to Vatican city with Sistine Chapel &nbsp;&amp; Rome city tour. Overnight in Rom</p>', '54d078b7e9337day1.jpg'),
(272, 50, 'Day 2: Rome to Florence', '<p>Rome to Florence</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Breakfast at hotel &amp; check out from the hotel. Later proceed for Pisa Tour. Check in to hotel, later proceed for Florence city tour. Overnight in Florence</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '54d07aa66c38cday2.jpg'),
(273, 50, 'Day 3: Florence to Venice(260 km)', '<p>Florence to Venice &nbsp; (260 km)</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Breakfast at hotel &amp; check out from the hotel. Later proceed to Venice. Arrive Venice &amp; Check into hotel. Later enjoy half Day to Murano, Burano &amp; Torcello. Overnight in Venice</p>', '54d07aef78d6fday3.jpg'),
(274, 50, 'Day 4: Venice-Postojna–Ljubljana–Zagreb(400Km)', '<p>Venice - Postojna &ndash; Ljubljana &ndash; Zagreb &nbsp; &nbsp;(400Km)</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Breakfast at hotel &amp; check out from the hotel. Proceed to Postojna City tour. Later proceed to Ljubljana city tour &amp; Zagreb City tour. Overnight in Zagreb</p>', '54d07b5adbde3day4.jpg'),
(275, 50, 'Day 5:  Zagreb–Visit belttown & proceed to Budapest(360 Km)', '<p style="text-align: left;">Zagreb &ndash; Visit belttown &amp; proceed to Budapest (360 Km)</p>\n<p>Breakfast at hotel &amp; check out from the hotel. Proceed to belt town tour. Later proceed to Budapest. Overnight in Budapest</p>', '54d07be1de480day5.jpg'),
(276, 50, 'Day 6: Budapest to Vienna  Bratisalava 280 km', '<p>Budapest to Vienna &nbsp;Bratisalava 280 km</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Breakfast at hotel &amp; check out from the hotel. Proceed to Budapest city tour. Later proceed to Vienna. Overnight in Vienna</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '54d07c19bcb4fday6.jpg'),
(277, 50, 'Day 7: Vienna to Munich(Salisburk 450Km)', '<p>Vienna to Munich(Salisburk 450Km)</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Breakfast at hotel &amp; check out from the hotel. Proceed to Vienna city tour. Later proceed to Munich. Overnight in Munich</p>', '54d07c658adf3day7.jpg'),
(278, 50, ' Day 8:  Munich to Zurich', '<p>Munich to Zurich</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Breakfast at hotel &amp; check out from the hotel. Proceed to Munich city tour. Later proceed to Zurich Overnight in zurich</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '54d07ca54f614day8.jpg'),
(279, 50, 'Day 9: Zurich – Mt Titlis–Interlaken city tour–Zurich City Tour', '<p>Zurich &ndash; Mt Titlis &ndash; Interlaken city tour &ndash; Zurich City Tour</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Breakfast at hotel &amp; check out from the hotel. Proceed to Mt Titlis, Interlaken city tour. Overnight in Dijon</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '54d07cf429d07day9.jpg'),
(280, 50, ' Day 10: Dijon  to Paris', '<p>Dijon &nbsp;to Paris</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Breakfast at hotel &amp; check out from the hotel. Proceed to Zurich City Tour. Arrive Paris &amp; enjoy a Paris city tour. Overnight in Paris</p>', '54d07d2528f4cday10.jpg'),
(281, 50, 'Day 11: 03rd Nov 2014–Departure Paris', '<p>03rd Nov 2014 &ndash; Departure Paris</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Breakfast at hotel &amp; check out and proceed to airport</p>', '54d07d8b1ff5fday11.jpg'),
(282, 51, 'Day 1', '<p style="text-align: left;">Tuesday, Rome, Arrive in Fiumicino airport (Italy), transfer to hotel. Rest of the day Rome site seeing (depends the arrival timings)San Giovanni, San Paolo, Santa Maria Maggiore and St. Peters Basilica, The four basilicas in Rome, and catacomb After dinner return to hotel for overnight stay &nbsp; with your tour director</p>', '54d0864257473day1.jpg'),
(283, 51, 'Day 2', '<p style="text-align: left;">Wednesday also in Rome 8.30 am transferred to the St Peters square for the Pope audience after that visit to the Vatican Museums and Michelangelos breathtaking Sistine Chapel. Stroll through St. Peters Square, passing Berninis famous colonnade, to visit St. Peters Basilica, where you will view Michelangelos Pieta. This highly-finished marble sculpture depicts the body of Jesus in the arms of Mary after the Crucifixion, and is considered one of the most powerfully moving works of art in the Western world, than visit colosseo after dinner return to hotel for overnight stay &nbsp; with your tour director.</p>', '54d08687a4fa3day2.jpg'),
(284, 51, 'Day 3:  Rome–Pisa–Florence.', '<p>&nbsp;Rome&ndash;Pisa&ndash;Florence.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Vistas of undulating hills, austere rows of cypress trees, terraced vineyards, olive groves, and rural villages form the backdrop of your journey through beautiful Tuscany. Take a break in Pisa to see the Square of Miracles and the amazing Leaning Tower, then on to Florence.</p>', '54d0871e027cbday3.jpg'),
(285, 51, 'Day 4 : Florence–Venice Area.', '<p>Florence&ndash;Venice Area.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Birthplace of the Renaissance, Florence was for centuries a leading power. On the included walking tour with an expert Local Guide, discover the landmarks of this amazing city, like Piazza Signoria with the Loggia dei Lanzi, Palazzo Vecchio, and the breathtaking cathedral on Piazza del Duomo. Later, watch how leather is embossed with gold, and enjoy free time to shop. In the afternoon, drive north across the River Po into the Plains of Veice.</p>', '54d0874e2d8efday4.jpg'),
(286, 51, 'Day 5 : Venice Area.', '<p>Venice Area.</p>\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Venice is known worldwide for its carnival and its film festival. Today, reach Venice by private motorboat to view the Bridge of Sighs and the Doges Palace plus St. Marks Basilica before the visit to a glassblowing factory. Don&rsquo;t miss out on the optional gondola trip, gliding along the picturesque canals with a local troubadour to serenade you.</p>', '54d087dea9b9bday5.jpg'),
(287, 51, 'Day 6 : Venice Area–Cortina–Innsbruck, Austria.', '<p>Venice Area&ndash;Cortina&ndash;Innsbruck, Austria.</p>\n<p>Leave the plains of the Veneto region behind and drive northwards to spot the spectacular peaks of the Dolomites. Stop awhile in Cortina to enjoy the grand scenery. Later, cross over the Europa Bridge and Brenner Pass into Austria to reach Innsbruck in time to see the the famous Golden Roof, emblem of the city.</p>', '54d0886edb23fday6.jpg'),
(288, 51, 'Day 7: Innsbruck–Liechtenstein–Lucerne, Switzerland.', '<p>Innsbruck&ndash;Liechtenstein&ndash;Lucerne, Switzerland.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Drive through the valleys and villages of the mountainous Tyrol to the Arlberg tunnel, descending into Switzerland. Stop briefly in Vaduz, Liechtenstein&rsquo;s capital. Majestic alpine scenery and glimpses of Lake Walen enchant you on the way to Lucerne.&nbsp;</p>', '54d0889e688f6day7.jpg'),
(289, 51, 'Day 8: Lucerne.', '<p>Lucerne.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;One of Switzerland&rsquo;s finest cities nestled amid its snowcapped Alps, surrounded by its lake, and embellished by the clear mountain waters of the River Reuss. The orientation includes the Lion Monument, erected in memory of the 800 Swiss Guards who defended Louis XVI and his wife at the wooden Chapel Bridge. A grand selection of optional activities completes the day: a cable-car ride to the 10,000-foot summit of Mount Titlis; a cruise on the fjord-like lake; and, of course, time to shop for that very Swiss watch.&nbsp;</p>', '54d088ca91e96day8.jpg'),
(290, 51, 'Day 9:  Lucerne–Paris, France.', '<p>Lucerne&ndash;Paris, France.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Vistas of green pastures and attractive chalets with rustic timbering and luxuriant flowers. Then, into France on the highway, past some of its most famous vineyards, to Paris. Arrive in time to enjoy the optional cabaret show.&nbsp;</p>', '54d088fabf90aday9.jpg'),
(291, 51, 'Day 10:  Paris.', '<p>Paris is a world-class city that probably has more familiar landmarks than almost any other city in the world. This morning, see them during the included city tour. View the famous Arc de Triomphe, Op&eacute;ra, Eiffel Tower, Champs Elys&eacute;es, and much more with a Local Guide. In the afternoon, feel like a French aristocrat as you join the optional walking tour through the immense Palace of Versailles. Tonight, consider joining the optional farewell dinner. (B)</p>', '54d0893707379day10.jpg'),
(292, 51, 'Day 11: Paris', '<p style="text-align: left;">Have a very hearty breakfast at the hotel. Pack your bags with a promise to return once again. On time our representative will transfer you to the Airport to board your flight &nbsp;with sweet memories</p>', '54d0896ad7b7dday11.jpg'),
(293, 52, 'DAY 1: HALF DAY CITY TOUR  ', '<p>HALF DAY CITY TOUR &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Arrive in Fiumicino airport transferred to Roma for half day city tour visit San Giovanni, Santa scale, and &nbsp;Santa Maria Maggiore &nbsp;After dinner proceed to hotel for overnight stay(Depends the arriving timings)Dinner only</p>', '54d0a87407e17day1.jpg'),
(294, 52, 'DAY 2: FULL DAY CITY TOUR', '<p>FULL DAY CITY TOUR.&nbsp;After breakfast St Peter&rsquo;s square, Vatican Museums, Michelangelos breathtaking Sistine Chapel. Stroll through St. Peters Square, passing Berninis famous colonnade, to visit St. Peters Basilica, where you will view Michelangelos Pieta. After lunch, Basilica San Paolo, &nbsp; Coliseum etc.., Overnight stay in Rome (Bf and dinner)</p>', '54d0a8cc0a658day2.jpg'),
(295, 52, 'DAY 3: PISA-FLORENCE', '<p>PISA-FLORENCE &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Pisa the wonders of the World&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;After breakfast proceeds to Pisa, the wonders of the world The Leaning Tower of Pisa is the campanile, or freestanding bell tower, of the cathedral of the Italian city of Pisa, known worldwide for its unintended tilt to one side. It is situated behind the Cathedral and is the third oldest structure in Pisas Cathedral Square after the Cathedral and the Baptistery. The towers tilt began during construction, caused by an inadequate foundation on ground too soft on one side to properly support the structures weight. The tilt increased in the decades before the structure was completed, and gradually increased until the structure was stabilized (and the tilt partially corrected) by efforts in the late 20th and early 21st centuries. The height of the tower is 55.86 m (183.27 ft) from the ground on the low side and 56.70 m (186.02 ft) on the high side. The width of the walls at the base is 4.09 m (13.42 ft) and at the top 2.48 m (8.14 ft). Its weight is estimated at 14,500 metric tons (16,000 short tons)</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;After lunch proceed to Florence. Florence is the birthplace of the Italian language the Renaissance and opera. A guided sightseeing of Florence introduces you to the citys Renaissance splendor. Marvel at Brunelleschi&rsquo;s masterpiece&mdash;Florence&rsquo;s massive pink white and green Duomo complemented by Giotto&rsquo;s Campanile. Then discover the church of Santa Croce where the tombs of Galileo and Michelangelo as well as the Dante Memorial are displayed. You&rsquo;ll also see the Palazzo Signoria which serves as an open air gallery of ancient and Renaissance statues. Right time turn back to hotel for overnight stay at Hotel Park California or Similar in Florence (Bf and dinner)</p>', '54d0a927c6674day3.jpg');
