(296, 52, 'Day 4: Florence-Venice city tour 260 km', '<p>Florence-Venice city tour 260 km</p>\n<p>&nbsp;Early morning proceed to Padua for visit St Antony&rsquo;s church 1 hour in Padua then Venice Island. &nbsp;Boat ride to the Island of Murano known throughout the world for its glass manufacturing industry. Visit St. Marks Square to begin a guided walking tour of romantic Venice. View the Golden Basilica of San Marco, the Bridge of Sighs and visit the Doges Palace, whose facade features a massive late-Gothic gate, known as the Porte Della carta , Rest of the day to exploring Venice only your own Optional: Gondola Ride with Music .After lunch proceed to Postojna cave and castle (Slovenia) 200 km</p>\n<p>&nbsp; The largest cave in the karts region and most visited show cave in all of Europe, words on a page can hardly do justice to the majesty of Postojna. So far, more than 20 kilometers of galleries have been found, of which barely a fraction are open to the public. All the same, a visit here still takes up much of a morning or an afternoon, as you make your way through the most spectacular parts of the cave, at first by a dinky little narrow-gauge train, and then on foot. There are no stairs or difficult climbs along the path to or inside the cave, so visitors with limited mobility should not have any difficulties. Overnight stay &nbsp;Postojna (Bf and dinner)</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '54d0a95d976e4day4.jpg'),
(297, 52, 'Day 5: Postojna-Ljubljana-Zagreb-Nagykanizsa, 332 Km', '<p>Postojna--- Ljubljana--- Zagreb-- Nagykanizsa, &nbsp;332 Km</p>\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Ljubljana, the capital of Slovenia, is a central European city that lies between the Alps and the Adriatic Sea in a basin where the Ljubljanica &nbsp;river flows into the Sava. Being the capital, it has all the modern facilities, yet has preserved its small-town friendliness and relaxed atmosphere. It is a vibrant city that is full of surprises.</p>\n<p>&nbsp; After breakfast, enjoy a walking tour of Zagreb through the fortified, medieval Upper Town, St. Marks Church with its multicolor tiled roof, Parliament and Government Palace. This evening enjoy dinner at the hotel in &nbsp;Nagykanizsa, Hungary &nbsp;and overnight stay .</p>', '54d0a9ba9e790day5.jpg'),
(298, 52, 'Day 6 :NAGYKANIZSA-BALATON LAKE-BUDAEPEST 230 Km', '<p>NAGYKANIZSA- BALATON LAKE &ndash; BUDAEPEST 230 Km</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Included sightseeing features Buda Castle, which dominates the twin cities of Buda and Pest that are separated by the broad ribbon of the Danube. Also see Heroes&rsquo; Square, which typifies the modern capital, the old inns and along the riverbank, Parliament, Margaret Island, Fishermen&rsquo;s Bastion, the Royal Castle, and Matthias Coronation Church. There&rsquo;s plenty more to do and see during these two days. Maybe try one of the historic spas!&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '54d0aa23a041aday6.jpg'),
(299, 52, 'Day 7:BUEPEST-BRATISALAVA-VIENNA 300 KM', '<p>BUEPEST --- BRATISALAVA-VIENNA 300 KM</p>\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Journey south east by way of Brno into the new state of Slovakia for a stop in its capital, Bratislava. An orientation tour in Bratisalava then proceed to Vienna</p>\n<p>VIENNA</p>\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;The highlight of today&rsquo;s itinerary will be the Vienna Woods and Mayerling. See the hunting lodge, the scene of the tragic 1889 death of Archduke Rudolf and his 17-year-old lover, Maria Vetsera. Later, a short drive to&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;The &nbsp;whole days to fully enjoy one of Europe&rsquo;s best known and loved capitals. Whatever your plans, it is wise to start off with the included city sightseeing tour. See the State Opera, Parliament, and the Town Hall. Stroll in Heroes&rsquo; Square to view the Hofburg. Splendid baroque palaces and the Viennese traditional joie de vivre give great scope for a program of optional excursions. Your stay is long enough to fit in your personal plans and choices.</p>', '54d0aa7d29cb0day7.jpg'),
(300, 52, 'DAY 8 :VIENNA-PRAGUE-300 KM', '<p>VIENNA-- PRAGUE-300 KM</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; The city has a wealth of gothic and baroque architecture that perhaps inspired Dvorak and Smetana, both Prague composers. The included guided sightseeing features landmarks such as the Jewish Quarter, Charles Bridge, and the Old Town Square with the Astronomical Clock. Plenty of time for some individual exploring, or maybe just a walk along the banks of the Vltava River and then a meal at a restaurant of your choice. Your second day in Prague will give you a program of optional excursions or, if you prefer, the opportunity for arranging your own day with visits to places of particular personal interest. overnight stay in Prague</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '54d0aae1a3bc9day8.jpg'),
(301, 52, 'DAY 9: PRAUGE-MUNICH 390KM', '<p>PRAUGE-- MUNICH 390KM</p>\n<p>&nbsp;Don&rsquo;t miss out on the included city sightseeing excursion with a Local Guide. You&rsquo;ll be taken through the historic center of Mozart&rsquo;s hometown to see its many highlights, including the Domplatz, the Horse Trough, Festival Hall, and, of course, the charming Getreidegasse where Mozart was born. This afternoon, motor directly to Munich. This evening, join the optional Bavarian evening and farewell dinner.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '54d0ab5971b01day9.jpg'),
(302, 52, 'DAY 10: MUNICH-VAZUZ-ENGLBERG-404 Km', '<p>MUNICH-VAZUZ-ENGLBERG&mdash;404 Km</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;This morning, tour Munich and view the major sights of the city, in particular, Nymphenburg Palace, former summer palace of the Wittlesbach dynasty. Continue via the Olympic Stadium to view many of the famous squares, including the delightful Marienplatz to see the Glockenspiel clock with its playful mechanical figures. Here you can begin exploring the largest and most famous Christmas market of Munich. This afternoon is free to further explore the over 20 Christmas markets located throughout the city</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '54d0ab8ba95a9day10.jpg'),
(303, 52, 'DAY 11: ENGLBERG', '<p>ENGLBERG</p>\n<p>Lugarno -Titles, Engel berg, Svizzera &nbsp;190km&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; After a hot lunch at Panorama restaurant in Mt.Titlis you will visit the world famous Mt. Titlis. On a hair &ndash;raising and unforgettable ride to the top of Swiss Alps at 3020 m /10000 ft (30 K.M). You will switch three different cable cars, and be amazed as the scenery changes from green meadows and scenic lakes to snow clad mountains. The last leg of the ride is one of the famous Rotair, which is the world&rsquo;s first revolving cable car, on which you will get an incredibly panoramic view of the surrounding glaciers, mountains and scenery. Dinner and overnight stay in Hotel Terrace or similar &nbsp;in Zurich</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '54d0abde9c660day11.jpg'),
(304, 52, 'DAY12: ZURICH AIRPORT', '<p>ZURICH AIRPORT</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Have a very hearty breakfast at the hotel. Pack your bags with a promise to return once again. On time our representative will transfer you to the Airport or Railway Station to board your flight or train with sweet memories of Rome</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '54d0ac24411e3day12.jpg'),
(305, 53, 'DAY 1Rome', '<p>Rome.&nbsp;Arrive in Fiumicino airport (Italy), transfer to hotel. Rest of the day Rome site seeing (depends the arrival timings) San Giovanni, San Paolo, Santa Maria Maggiore and St. Peters Basilica the four basilicas in Rome, with highly-finished marble sculpture depicts the body of Jesus in the arms of Mary after the Crucifixion, and is considered one of the most powerfully moving works of art your tour director. After dinner return to hotel for overnight stay &nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '54d0af3c4f8f1day1.jpg'),
(306, 53, 'DAY 2', '<p style="text-align: left;">&nbsp;Also in Rome 8.30 am transferred to the St Peters square for the Pope audience after that visit to the Vatican Museums and Michelangelos breathtaking Sistine Chapel. Stroll through St. Peters Square, passing Berninis famous colonnade, to visit St. Peters Basilica, where you will view Michelangelos Pieta, This in the Western world, after dinner return to hotel for overnight stay with your tour director</p>', '54d0af5d3a2fdday2.jpg'),
(307, 53, 'DAY 3:Roma-Pisa 340 km and Florence city tour 80 km', '<p>Roma- Pisa 340 km and Florence city tour 80 km</p>\n<p>Morning travel through the stunning panorama of &nbsp;to Pisa. En route, view the famous Piazza del Miracle with its Leaning Tower, the Baptistery, The Duomo, and the Monumental Cemetery. The four monuments of this extraordinary piazza make for a unique architectural blend of Romanesque and Gothic styles.Evening visit to the Academia of Fine Arts, where Michelangelos David is housed. Walk to the Duomo, celebrated for its magnificent dome designed by Brunelleschi, and view the Baptisterys renowned "Gates of Paradise" by Ghiberti. Continue to explore the open air art museum of Signora Square ending at Ponte Vecchio, known as the "Old Bridge." Enjoy the afternoon at leisure in this spectacular Renaissance city. After dinner overnight stay at Florence .</p>', '54d0afa5a719dday3.jpg'),
(308, 53, 'DAY 4:Florence-Venice city tour 260 km', '<p><strong>Florence-Venice city tour 260 km</strong></p>\n<p>Early morning boat ride to the Island of Murano known throughout the world for its glass manufacturing industry. Visit St. Marks Square to begin a guided walking tour of romantic Venice. View the Golden Basilica of San Marco, the Bridge of Sighs and visit the Doges Palace, whose facade features a massive late-Gothic gate, known as the Porte Della carta , Rest of the day to exploring Venice only your own Optional: Gondola Ride with Music&nbsp;</p>', '54d0afe4c3ed2day4.jpg'),
(309, 53, 'DAY 5:Venice- Postojna cave and castle (Slovenia) 200 km- Ljubljana (Slovenia) 6okm', '<p>Venice- Postojna cave and castle (Slovenia) 200 km- Ljubljana (Slovenia) 6okm</p>\n<p>The largest cave in the karts region and most visited show cave in all of Europe, words on a page can hardly do justice to the majesty of Postojna. So far, more than 20 kilometers of galleries have been found, of which barely a fraction are open to the public. All the same, a visit here still takes up much of a morning or an afternoon, as you make your way through the most spectacular parts of the cave, at first by a dinky little narrow-gauge train, and then on foot. There are no stairs or difficult climbs along the path to or inside the cave, so visitors with limited mobility should not have any difficulties. &nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Depart to Ljubljana, a vibrant city with rich historical heritage and traditions. Visit the old centre with unique mixture of Baroque and Art Nouveau architectural appearance. Proceed to Zagreb for dinner and overnight stay.&nbsp;</p>', '54d0b02fca76dday5.jpg'),
(310, 53, 'DAY 6:Ljubljana-Vienna-(Austria) 382km', '<p>Ljubljana- Vienna-(Austria) 382km</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;Vienna. Morning sightseeing with a Local Guide starts with vistas of Prater Park with its giant Ferris wheel and the United Nations City on the banks of the Danube River. Then, drive along Ring Boulevard, pass the State Opera House and the Jewish quarter, and stop at the Hofburg Palace, winter residence of the Austrian Imperial family. Marvel at the impressive courtyards and famous Heldenplatz, and visit ST. STEPHEN&acirc;S CATHEDRAL. An optional excursion to Sch&Atilde;&para;nbrunn Palace and an evening out to one of Vienna&rsquo;s concert halls can be arranged.</p>', '54d0b15e7fe63day6.jpg'),
(311, 53, 'DAY 7:Vienna-Budapest (Hungary) 250km', '<p>&nbsp;Vienna -Budapest (Hungary) 250km</p>\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Breakfast in the hotel than 3-hour-long city tour and Parliament visit. Erzsebet Square, Opera House, Heroes Square/millennium Memorial (photo stop), downtown, Erzsebet Bridge, panorama view to the banks of the River Danube with famous public buildings, panorama view from Gellert Hill (photo stop), walk in the Castle district, Matthias Church (outside), Fishermen Bastion, panorama view to the city, Margit Bridge.</p>\n<p>Visit the House of Parliament: first outside then inside the impressive building with its magnificent neogothic chambers and staircases, the home of the Hungarian Holy Crown. The program ends in front of the House of Parliament. (Note: this tour maybe changed to a city tour by boat, inquire for details)</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;Overnight in Budapest</p>', '54d0b19aee6c4day7.jpg'),
(312, 53, ' DAY 8:Budapest Timisoara, Timi?, Romania 287 km', '<p>Budapest Timisoara, Timi?, Romania 287 km</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Across the town centre is the picturesque Habsburg-era Piata Unirii, so-named for the imposing sight of the Romano-Catholic and Serbian Orthodox Cathedrals facing each other. Historic pastel-hued buildings line the square. During the 18th century, this was the citys commercial centre and the venue for numerous military processions and religious ceremonies.</p>', '54d0b1f0bb42aday8.jpg'),
(313, 53, 'Day 9:Timisoara-Sibiu (Romania) 276km', '<p>Timisoara- Sibiu (Romania) 276km</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;In the morning sightseeing tour of Sibiu, the European Capital of Culture in 2007. During the visit you will pass through the old streets to admire the main monuments, such as the Bruckenthal Palace in Baroch style from the late XVIIIth century, the infamous Liers bridge built over a road that connects the lower city with the upper city, the Saxons Cathedral erected at the beginning of the XVIth century that preserves a precious fresco of the Crucifixion from 1445, the Catholic Cathedral in German Baroch style built at the beginning of the XVIIIth century, the main places of the city ( the Big Square, the Little Square and the Huet Square) and Christian Orthodox Cathedral, the seat of Transylvanias Metropoly &nbsp;Afterwards departure to Alba Iulia, the historical and spiritual capital of Romania, where on 1st December 1918 was proclaimed the national unity between Transylvania and Romania with the name of Great Romania. Visit of the citadel of Alba Iulia, in Vauban style, the Cathedral of the Unification, a beautiful Roman-Catholic with Wallachian and Moldavian elements</p>', '54d0b2417350aday9.jpg'),
(314, 53, ' Day 10:Sibiu- Brasov (Romania) 150km', '<p>Sibiu- Brasov (Romania) 150km</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;In the morning guided tour of the city of Brasov, an important medieval cultural center, where in the XVI th century were printed the first books in Romania. Starting from the splendid Council Square we will make a tour of the historic center, enriched by particular civic and religious buildings, such as the Black Church, the largest Gothic church in Romania, the Council House a building from the XVth century, rebuilt after the great fire of 1689 in baroque style, the St. Nicolae Church that combines the Gothic style in the exterior to the Byzantine style in the interior and the Museum of the First Romanian School from Scheii Brasovului, that hides a great treasure of old books and manuscripts, the Ecaterina and Schei Gates. Departure to Bran Castle ( known as Draculas castle ), a real fortress built upon a rock. Vlad used this castle as headquarters for his incursions into Transylvania. Then we arrive on Prahova Valley and Sinaia "the pearl of the Carpathians". Here we visit the most beautiful castle in Romania, in Bavarian style, the summer residence of King Carol I - the Peles Castle. Nearby there is the Pelisor Castle - built for Ferdinand and Mary Departure to Bran Castle ( known as Draculas castle ), a real fortress built upon a rock. Vlad used this castle as headquarters for his incursions into Transylvania. Then we arrive on Prahova Valley and Sinaia "the pearl of the Carpathians". Here we visit the most beautiful castle in Romania, in Bavarian style, the summer residence of King Carol I - the Peles Castle. Nearby there is the Pelisor Castle - built for Ferdinand and Mary</p>', '54d0b2897326aday10.jpg'),
(315, 53, 'DAY 11', '<p>&nbsp;Morning returns back to Budapest and city tour after dinner overnight stay here&nbsp;</p>', '54d0b2b6d427fday11.jpg'),
(316, 53, 'Day 12 ', '<p>After breakfast Depart four your destination transfer to the Venice Marco Polo airport to board return flight to your</p>', '54d0b2d9f28bcday12.jpg'),
